<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="1PE" stage="Rev" version="A">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 04:07:43Z" when="2009-10-02 04:07:43Z" stage="Draft">drafted by Pdt. Max Jacob; draft revised by C. Grimes; advisors C&amp; B Grimes; with primary reference to HCE, NLT, NRSV, Ex. Summ; worked with team (June, Mus, Adriana) in Darwin Aug 2006, read-through with June's comments; plus read-through pass with Barbara's comments; UNS check in Kupang, August 2006; Consultant checked by Marge Crofts in Kupang, 13-14 September 2006; Read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana; Further tightening from Tetun (NS) and Helong (DG) checks, plus Barbara's further suggestions (versi T);</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 11:18:45Z" when="2014-02-24 11:18:45Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 13-14 September 2006 in Kupang; Consultant: Marge Crofts, approved. Report: KM-John-2Cor-ConsRep.doc; 1 Peter issues for Kupang NT CEG.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-22 03:53:16Z" when="2015-01-22 03:53:16Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read through for Kupang mini-Bible with Chuck, Lena, Rina, Oma at UBB. BackTrans also adjusted.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">1 Petrus</p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">1 Petrus<bt>1 Petrus</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Petrus pung surat partama<bt>Petrus' first letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Salam<bt>Greetings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1-2" />Ini surat dari beta, Petrus, andia Yesus Kristus pung utusan.<bt>This letter is from me, Petrus, that is Yesus Kristus' *apostle (sent/commissioned one)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta tulis ini surat kasi bosong samua yang Tuhan Allah su pili ame. Bosong jadi orang asing yang ada idop tasiar pi banya tampa di propinsi Pontus, propinsi Galatia, propinsi Kapadokia, propinsi Asia, deng propinsi Bitinia.<bt>I write this letter to all of you whom God has chosen/selected. You are foreigners who are living scattered in many places in the province of Pontus, the province of Galatia, the province of Kapadokia, the province of Asia, and the province of Bitinia.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apostolos: apostle, messenger, missionary, a group"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">apostolos: apostle, messenger, missionary, a group of honored believers who had a special function, authorized agent, authorized representative eklektos: chosen, elect, select, choice, picked<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>parepidemos: stranger, exile, foreigner, refugee, settled temporarily, one passing through a territory with no intention of permanent residence diaspora: dispersion, scattered, the place in which the scattered ones are<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERAL: Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ to the chosen exiles scattered in Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Sodara sayang dong! Dari mula-mula, Allah Bapa su pili memang sang bosong ko jadi Dia pung orang. Dia pung Roh ju bekin bosong jadi barisi kasi sang Dia, ko biar bosong bisa bekin iko samua parenta yang Yesus Kristus ada kasi sang bosong. Deng kalo bosong bekin iko Dia pung parenta samua, itu sama ke Tuhan ada parcík Yesus pung dara di bosong, ko jadi tanda bilang, bosong su jadi barisi kasi sang Dia.<bt>Dear siblings! From the beginning, Father God has chosen you-pl beforehand to be/become His people. His Spirit also makes you be/become *clean/pure/holy for Him, so that you can do according to/obey all the commands which Yesus Kristus has/is giving to you. And if/when you do according to /obey all of His commands, that is like God2 is sprinkling Yesus' blood on you, as a sign that you have become clean/pure/holy for Him. [EXEG: NRSV, NLT, HCE, CEV, Ex. Summ. Very complex verse. In Gk. vs.1 has no verb. ‘Chosen’ is an adjective modifying ‘exiles’. The general consensus is the prepositional phrases in vs.2 link back to “chosen”. The prep phrases are a) “according to the foreknowledge of God the Father” b) “in/by sanctification of the Spirit” c-1) “(resulting) in obedience [to Christ-NRSV, NLT, CEV, HCE, TB, Ex. Summ #1]” c-2) “and (resulting) in sprinkling of the blood of Jesus Christ”. Some see a special agency of God the Father choosing us, and then assigning particular work to each other member of the Trinity. I.e. He had the Spirit make you become holy for obedience to Christ, and He had Christ die to cleanse/atone for us/our sins, alluding to the OT priestly sprinkling of the blood. Most translations don't try to make this high-level agency link (e.g. NRSV, NLT, CEV, TB, etc.) which is one possible reading of the complex Gk text. NIV does, but it's structure is too dense to be able to reflect it in the grammars of the local lgs. The problem with breaking it up and saying “He had His Spirit make you become holy...” and “He had Christ die to cleanse us...” breaks up the Trinity, coming across in local lgs as a hierarchical relationship of separate and distinct beings. Our current rendering (supported by the sources cited above) is a compromise that doesn't force the reading, and doesn't skew the focus. NOTE also that local cultures have traditional atonement ceremonies involving sprinkling the blood of sacrificed animals (on a post, into the sea, etc.) It's possible that the phrase “sprinkling Jesus' blood” doesn't evoke this atonement picture for some young city kids, but it does for most people in NTT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parcík = sprinkle (by hand), as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">parcík = sprinkle (by hand), as in water on clothes to be ironed, api parcík kaluar (dari busi) ; semprot (pake alat) ; ujan parcík = the spray/splatter of rain hitting the ground ; also fine mist of motorcycle spray going by in the rain *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta sambayang ko Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong, ko biar bosong bisa idop tamba hari, tamba aman, dame, deng tanáng.<bt>I pray that God will show His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you, so that you can live increase day, increase safe (external peace), peace (relational), and calm (inner peace).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prognoosis: foreknowledge, plan, purpose, destined, prediction"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">prognoosis: foreknowledge, plan, purpose, destined, prediction hagiasmos: holiness, consecration, sanctification, the state of being made holy, set apart for God, set apart from the world for the service of God<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>hypakoee: obedience, submission rantismos: sprinkling, cleansing<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>kharis: favor, grace, gift, kindness, gracious care, gracious help eireenee: peace, welfare, health, soundness, harmony<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>plethunoo: increase, multiply, be full, become abundant, grow LITERAL: according to the knowledge beforehand of God the Father, by the work of the Spirit to set you apart for God, to obey him and be sprinkled by the blood of Jesus Christ; may favor and peace increase for you.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo kotong parcaya sang Tuhan, kotong basandar di Dia<bt>If/when we-inc believe in God2, we depend/lean on Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Samua puji kasi sang Tuhan Allah! Dia tu, kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus pung Bapa. Tagal Tuhan pung hati mas, andia ko Dia talalu kasian sang kotong. Yesus Kristus mati, ais Dia idop kambali. Jadi kalo Kristus bekin kotong idop, Dia kasi kotong idop baru, sama ke kotong lahir kambali. Andia ko kotong parcaya sang Kristus tarús, te kotong baharap deng yakin bilang, Dia nanti jaga deng piara bae-bae sang kotong.<bt>All praises to God! He is our-inc Bos Yesus Kristus' Father. Because of God2's nobleness/kindness, that is why He so much pities/mercy/loves2 us. Yesus Kristus died, and then He came back to life. So (consequently), if/when Kristus makes us live, He gives us new life, like we are born again. That is why we-inc keep on believing in Kristus, cuz (elaboration) we hope with assurance/confidence, that He will care for/look after us well. [EXEG: on ‘mercy’ CEV went too generic with ‘good’, and TB went to Arabic /rahmat/] [NOTE to daughter translation: ALT: He let Yesus Kristus die and then live again so as to give us new life, (But note in the Gk the agency for the death and resurrection is completely out of focus, as in the current rendering of KM. Main point: God has given us new birth. How? through the death and resurrection of JC (irrespective of whether God was the agent or JC-both appear in scripture). Why? because of God's great mercy.)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eulogetos: praised, blessed, well-spoken of eleos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">eulogetos: praised, blessed, well-spoken of eleos: mercy, compassion, pity, pity for the misery and bad condition of sinful men, sympathy<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>anagennaw: give birth to again, new birth, new life elpis: hope, expectancy, future good, wait for<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>zaw: live, be active, vigorous anastasis: resurrection<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>nekros: dead LITERAL: God be praised, who is the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who according to his great mercy has given us new birth for a living hope, through the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead,<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Di ini dunya, kalo satu bapa mati, na, dia kasi tenga dia pung harta sang dia pung ana-ana dong. Bagitu ju, Yesus su simpan pusaka kasi kotong di langit. Ma itu pusaka sonde bisa rusak, sonde bisa ancor, deng sonde bisa ilang buang.<bt>In this world, if/when a father dies, na, he leaves behind his possessions to his children. In the same way, Yesus has stored away possessions for us-inc in the sky/heaven. But those possessions cannot ruin/spoil/break down, cannot be destroyed, and cannot disappear/be lost. [NOTE to daughter trans: ALT (focus): He also has stored away inheritance for you-pl in the sky/*heaven. But, that inheritance is different from inheritance on earth, because [it] cannot ruin/spoil/break.down, cannot be destroyed, and cannot disappear/be.lost.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) /di ini dunya/ added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) /di ini dunya/ added to indicate that “obtaining the inheritance is in focus, not “upon death of the father”; It's Jesus who has stored this inheritance; second /harta/ changed to /pusaka/</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kleronomia: inheritance, possession, property received by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">kleronomia: inheritance, possession, property received by an heir aphthartos: imperishable, not decay, incorruptible, immortal, unchangeable<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>amiantos: undefiled, not ruined, unspoiled, unstained, not pollutable amarantos: unfading, not disappear, not lessen, not wither<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>terew: keep, store, reserve, hold, preserve LITERAL: to an inheritance which cannot be destroyed, or spoiled, or fade away, which is stored in heaven for you<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Bosong parcaya bilang, Tuhan Allah ada pung kuasa ko tolong ame sang bosong. Dia piara sang bosong, deng jaga sang bosong, ko jang ada yang bekin ancor sang bosong. Deng nanti kalo dunya kiamat, Dia mau kasi tunju Dia kasi salamat sang bosong deng cara karmana.<bt>You believe that God has power/authority to help/assist you-pl. He cares for/looks after you, and guards/protects you, so there is nothing that destroys you. And later when the world ends, He is going to show how (what way) He *saves you. [EXEG: Gk is very complex here with 2 intrumental phrases “by God's power (dative case) ... through faith (instrumental prep)”. KM handles this by “You believe a) God has power to help you, b) He cares for and protects you so nothing destroys you, and c) in the end He will show how He will save you. 6 That is why...”] [NOTE to daughter translations: Don't change this careful structure to combine the 1st two sentences and say “Because you believe...” That will stuff up the higher level structure. Don't make a verse bridge since we are not moving clause-level info into another verse.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dunamis: power, might phrourew: guard, hold"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">dunamis: power, might phrourew: guard, hold in custody, confine, protect, preserve<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>pistis: faith, belief, trust, persuasion swteria: salvation, deliverance, rescue<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>hetoime: ready, prepared beforehand apokaluptw: reveal, uncover, show, disclose, unveil<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>kairos: time, point of time or period of time esxatos: last, end, final<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERAL: By God's power you are protected through faith for salvation ready to be revealed in the end time.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Andia ko bosong pung hati sanáng, biar sakarang bosong rasa barát tagal bosong musti kaná susa macam-macam.<bt>That is why your livers are happy, even though now you feel heavy (sad, discouraged, depressed) because you must be effected by various sorts of difficulties/troubles.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agalliaw: be glad, rejoice, exult, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">agalliaw: be glad, rejoice, exult, be overjoyed oligos: little<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>arti: now, present time dei: it is necessary<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>lupew: grieve, mourn, be sad, sorrowful, be in pain, distressed, suffer poikilos: diversified, varied, various, many kinds<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>peirasmos: temptation, test, trial, hardship, peril, trouble, undeserved suffering from outside LITERAL: in which you are glad, though now for a little while it is necessary to be distressed by various hardships,<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Tuhan Allah kasi biar kotong dapa coba'an dong, ko mau uji kotong pung parcaya sang Dia. Kalo kotong lolos dari coba'an, itu kasi tunju bilang, kotong pung parcaya, kuat deng batúl. Kotong bisa banding deng mas. Te kotong musti kasi panas mas dalam api, ko biar dia pung kotoran kaluar dolo, baru kotong dapa mas tulen. Padahal iko Tuhan Allah pung pikir, kotong pung parcaya pung harga lebe mahal dari mas. Jadi kalo kotong pung parcaya lolos dari coba'an bagitu, nanti waktu Yesus Kristus datang kambali, Tuhan Allah ju puji sang kotong, ais Dia kasi tunju kotong pung hebat, deng Dia hormat sang kotong.<bt>God allows us to experience/encounter testing/ temptation/trials, to test our-inc faith in Him. If/when we pass/come through testing/temptation/trials, it shows that our faith is strong and true/correct/right. We-inc can compare (it) with gold. Cuz (elaboration) we must heat gold in fire, so that its dirt/crud comes out first, before we get pure gold. Whereas in fact, according to God's thinking, our faith is worth (price/value) far more than gold. So (consequently) if our faith passes/comes through the testing/temptation/trials like that, later when Yesus Kristus comes back, God will also praise us, and/then show our greatness/amazingness, and He (will) honour us. [EXEG: Gk: glory here; NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dokimion: test, genuineness, without imperfection polutimos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">dokimion: test, genuineness, without imperfection polutimos: valuable, precious<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>xrusion: gold apollumi: pass away, destroy, perish<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>puros: fire dokimazw: examine, test, refine<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>heuriskw: find epainos: praise<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>doksa: glory time: honor<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>apokalupsis: revelation, disclosure, uncovering LITERAL: so that the testing of your faith, which is more valuable than gold, which comes to an end even though it is refined by fire, may result in praise and glory and honor when Jesus Christ is revealed.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ini coba'an dong ni, ada pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Ini coba'an dong ni, ada pung maksud ko uji kotong pung parcaya sang Tuhan, ais kasi tunju bilang, kotong pung parcaya tu, kuat deng batúl. Kalo kotong lolos bagitu, itu kasi tunju, bilang, kotong pung parcaya tu, kuat deng batúl. Inga, te kalo kotong mau dapa mas tulen, kotong musti kasi panas itu mas dalam api, ko biar dia pung kotoran kaluar.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Biar bosong balóm lia langsung sang Yesus, ma bosong sayang sang Dia. Biar bosong sonde lia sang Dia sakarang, ma bosong parcaya sang Dia. Bosong ju ada pung hati babunga lebe-lebe, biar sonde ada kata yang pas ko kasi tau orang so'al bosong pung hati sanáng.<bt>Even if/though you-pl have not yet seen Yesus directly, nevertheless you love Him. Even though you don't see Him now, nevertheless you believe in Him. You also have excessively glad livers, even if there are no words that exactly fit (it) to explain/tell people about your happy livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agalliaoo: be glad, rejoice, exult khara:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">agalliaoo: be glad, rejoice, exult khara: joy<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>aneklaleetos: inexpressible, unutterable doksazoo: glorify, clothe in splendor<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERAL: You do not see him, but you love him. Even though you do not see him now, you believe and are glad with joy that cannot be described.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Tagal bosong parcaya sang Dia, bosong pung upa, andia Tuhan Allah kasi salamat sang bosong dari bosong pung sala.<bt>Because you-pl believe in Him, your reward is God saving your from your wrongs/sin. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV = yuck!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">CEV = yuck!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="komizoo: obtain, carry off, get, receive,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">komizoo: obtain, carry off, get, receive, bring telos: end, outcome, goal<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>psykhe: soul, life, the seat and center of life, person, central personality LITERAL: You receive the goal of faith, the salvation of your souls.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Tuhan Allah pung jubir dolu-dolu dong ada cari tau ko mau mangarti lebe bae, karmana Tuhan kasi salamat orang dari dong pung sala. Itu jubir dong kasi tau memang so'al Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong, tagal Dia su siap memang ko kasi salamat sang bosong.<bt>God's spokespeople long ago were trying to better understand how God2 saves people from their sins. Those spokespeople foretold about God2 showing His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you, because He was already prepared beforehand to save you. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekzetew: seek out, search for, look"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">ekzetew: seek out, search for, look for eksepaunaw: inquire carefully, find out more, investigate thoroughly<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>xaris: favor, grace, gift, kindness LITERAL: Concerning this salvation, the prophets inquired and searched carefully, who prophesied of the grace which would come to you,<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Kristus pung Roh ada karjá dalam dong pung hati ko kasi tau memang bilang, nanti Kristus musti kaná susa, deng jalan karmana Dia musti dapa sangsara. Ais itu samua, baru Tuhan angka tinggi-tinggi sang Dia. Andia ko jubir dong mau cari tau kapan ini hal dong jadi.<bt>Kristus' Spirit was working in their livers to tell beforehand that later Kristus must be effected by trouble/difficulty, and how He must suffer. And after all that only then would God *glorify (elevate way on high) Him. That is why those spokespeople wanted to find out when these things would happen. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: Gk is ambiguous: searching for who/what and when. We follow Ex. Summ. #3 here, and focus on what &amp; when, rather than who and when.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) split long sentence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) split long sentence</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eraunaw: search, inquire, examine, investigate poios:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">eraunaw: search, inquire, examine, investigate poios: of what kind<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>delow: reveal, make clear, show, signify promarturomai: predict,<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>pathema: suffering, misfortune, doksa: glory<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERAL: trying to find out the time and circumstances to which the Spirit of Christ in them was pointing when he predicted the sufferings of Christ and the glories that would follow.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Ais Kristus pung Roh, ju kasi tau sang itu jubir dong bilang, bukan dong yang lia, ma bosong yang dapa lia ini hal dong. Naa, sakarang bosong ju dapa dengar so'al ini hal dong, tagal Tuhan pung Roh Barisi dari sorga su kirim orang laen ko pi kasi tau Tuhan pung Kabar Bae sang bosong. Padahal Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga dong ju ada kapingin mau lia ini hal dong.<bt>So then Kristus' Spirit also told those spokespeople that not them, but you-pl would be the ones who would get to see these things. Naa [+shift], now you are also able to hear about these things, because God2's *Holy/Clean/Pure Spirit from heaven has sent other people to go tell God2's Good News to you. Whereas in fact, God2's *angels (underlings) from heaven also desire to see/experience these things. [EXEG: NLT; context of vs.10; “look into” LN learn more about, CEV know more about, NLT eagerly watching these things happen.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added yang lia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) added yang lia</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apokalyptoo: reveal, uncover diakoneoo: serve|i(12) (12)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">apokalyptoo: reveal, uncover diakoneoo: serve<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>anaggeloo: disclose euaggelizoo: preach<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>apostelloo: send away epithymeoo: desire<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>parakyptoo: look into LITERAL: It was revealed to them that they were serving not themselves but you, in the things which have now been announced to you by those who preached the good news through the Holy Spirit sent from heaven, things into which angels longed to look.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="itu hal dong sonde kaná sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">itu hal dong sonde kaná sang dong (waktu dong ada idop), ma lama-lama nanti jadi kaná sang bosong. Naa, sakarang bosong ju dapa dengar so'al itu hal dong, tagal Tuhan pung Roh Barisi dari langit su utus/suru/kirim orang (laen) ko pi kasi tau Tuhan pung Kabar Bae sang bosong. Padahal, Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga dong ju rindu/kapingin mau tau ini hal dong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan suru ko kotong idop barisi<bt>God2 orders for us-inc to live clean/pure/holy</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Andia ko bosong musti siap sadia ko mangarti bae-bae ini hal dong samua. Jaga bae-bae ko bosong pikir lurus. Siap sadia ko parcaya tarús sang Yesus Kristus sampe Dia datang kambali. Tagal itu waktu, Tuhan mau kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong.<bt>That is why you-pl must be (fully) prepared (doublet) to understand well all these things. Guard carefully so that you think straight/correct/righteous/honest. Be (fully) prepared to keep on believing in Yesus Kristus until He comes back. Because at that time, God2 is going to show His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anazwnnumi: bind up, gird up, prepare"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">anazwnnumi: bind up, gird up, prepare for action, remove all impediments osphus: waist, loins<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>dianoia: mind, disposition, thought, the faculty of knowing, understanding, or moral reflection nephw: be self controlled, sober, well-balanced, morally alert<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>teleiws: perfectly, fully, completely, altogether elpizw: hope, set your hope<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>pherw: bear, bring LITERAL: Therefore, prepare your minds for action, be self-controlled, set your hope completely on the favor that is coming to you when Jesus Christ is revealed.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Bosong musti dengar-dengar sang Tuhan Allah, sama ke ana-ana dengar-dengar sang dong pung mama-bapa. Dolu bosong balóm mangarti Tuhan pung jalan idop yang batúl. Ma sakarang bosong su mangarti. Jadi jang idop iko bosong pung kapingin bekin jahat lai. Te itu bosong pung jalan idop yang lama.<bt>You must keep listening to/obeying God, just like children keep listening to/obeying their mother-father. Previously you did not yet understand God2's true way of life. But now you already understand. So (consequently), don't live according to your desires to do evil anymore. Cuz (elaboration) that is your old way of life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dengar-dengar = UNS keep listening"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">dengar-dengar = UNS keep listening</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="syskheematizoo: formed like, be conformed to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">syskheematizoo: formed like, be conformed to proteros: earlier<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>agnoia: ignorance epithumia: desire<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERAL: As obedient children, do not be conformed to the passions of your former ignorance,</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Andia ko sakarang bosong musti idop barisi. Te Tuhan Allah tu, barisi. Dia yang pange ame sang bosong ko jadi Dia pung ana. Tagal itu, bosong musti barisi dalam bosong pung idop anteru.<bt>That is why now you must live clean/pure/holy. Cuz (elaboration) God2 is clean/pure/holy. He is the one who called/summoned you-pl to be/become His children. Because of that, you must be clean/pure/holy in your whole life (all aspects).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalew: call anastrophe: conduct|i(15) (15) |rginomai:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">kalew: call anastrophe: conduct<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>ginomai: be LITERAL: But as he who called you is holy, be holy yourselves in all your conduct,<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Te ada tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti barisi, tagal Beta barisi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it is written in the Scriptures saying, “You-pl must be clean/pure/holy, because I am clean/pure/holy.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: Since it is written, &quot;Be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: Since it is written, "Be holy, because I am holy."</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 11:44-45, 19:2, 20:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Bosong suka ba'omong deng Tuhan Allah sama ke Dia, bosong pung Bapa. Dia ju jadi Tukang Putus Parkara yang nanti pareksa tiap orang pung idop. Ma Dia beda dari tukang putus parkara yang laen dong. Te Dia putus orang pung parkara deng fer, deng sonde barát sablá. Andia ko bosong musti idop deng ati-ati. Te bosong sama ke orang asing yang tenga tahan di ini dunya sa.<bt>You like to talk with God like He is your Father. He is also the Judge who will examine each person's life. But He is different from other judges. Cuz (elaboration) He decides people's cases fairly, and is not biased/prejudiced. That is why you must live carefully. Cuz (elaboration) you are like a stranger/foreigner/outsider who just lives temporarily in this world. [EXEG: filled in ellipsed proposition “different from other judges” in response to UNS struggles.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ati-ati (stok lama) ~ hati-hati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">ati-ati (stok lama) ~ hati-hati</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epikalew: call upon aproswpolemptws: impartially|i(17) (17)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">epikalew: call upon aproswpolemptws: impartially<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>krinw: judge paroikia: sojourn, stay, live<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>anastrephw: live LITERAL: And if you call upon him as Father, the one who judges each one impartially according to his deeds, conduct yourselves with fear throughout the time of your exile.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Bosong su tau bilang, Kristus su bayar putus ko tabús ame sang bosong dari bosong pung idop yang sonde ada pung ujung-pohon. Itu idop model bagitu, bosong tarima ame dari bosong pung nene-moyang dong, sama ke satu harta pusaka. Ma inga te Kristus bayar kasi sang bosong sonde pake mas ko perak yang nanti ilang buang.<bt>You already know that Kristus has paid off/in full to *redeem/ransom you from your life that had/has no reason or purpose (idiom: tip-base [NOTE: botanical metaphor] -doublet). That life of that model/type/kind, you received from your ancestors, like an inheritance. But remember that Kristus paid for you not using gold or silver that will disappear (completely).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="poetry? phthartos: perishable|i(18) (18) |rargurion: silver"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">poetry? phthartos: perishable<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>argurion: silver khrusion: gold<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>lutrow: redeem mataios: idle, futile, waste of time<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>patroparadotos: inherited LITERAL: You know that you were ransomed from the futile ways inherited from your fathers, not with perishable things such as silver or gold,<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Ma Dia bayar kasi sang bosong pake Dia pung dara sandiri. Itu, mahal mau mati! Dia mati sama ke satu domba ana yang sonde parná bekin sala, yang dong horo jadi korban.<bt>But He paid for you using His own blood. Now that is really expensive/valuable! He died like a lamb (sheep offspring) that had never done wrong/sin, which they throat sliced/ritually slaughtered as a sacrifice.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="amwmos: umblemished, spotless, without defect, faultless"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">amwmos: umblemished, spotless, without defect, faultless aspilos: without blemish, without spot<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERAL: but with the precious blood of Christ, like that of a lamb without defect or spot.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Waktu Tuhan Allah balóm bekin ini dunya, Dia su tau memang samua yang nanti Kristus bekin. Ma dolu, Tuhan Allah balóm kasi tunju Kristus sang orang di ini dunya. Baru sakarang ni, Dia kasi tunju Kristus, ko jadi berkat kasi bosong.<bt>When God had not yet made this world (= before He created...), He already knew beforehand everything that Kristus would do. But previously God had not yet shown/revealed Kristus to the people in this world. Only now has He shown/revealed Kristus, to be a blessing for/to you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV shifts &quot;revealed&quot; to &quot;came&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">!@ CEV shifts "revealed" to "came" and "for your sake" to "because of you" ; sakarang-sakarang = recently</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proginwskw: know beforehand LITERAL: He was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">proginwskw: know beforehand LITERAL: He was known/chosen before the foundation of the world, but was revealed in these last times for your sake.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Tagal Kristus bekin bagitu, andia ko bosong bisa parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Te Dia su kasi idop kambali sang Kristus, deng angka tinggi-tinggi sang Dia. Tuhan Allah bekin bagitu ko biar bosong parcaya sang Dia, deng baharap ko Dia bekin iko apa yang Dia su janji memang.<bt>Because of what Kristus has done, you-pl are able to believe in God. Cuz (elaboration) He has brought Kristus back to life, and *glorified (elevated way up on high) Him. God did that so that you would believe in Him, and hope that He will do according to what He has already promised beforehand. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;bring back alive&quot; could imply that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">"bring back alive" could imply that he was not completely dead? CHECK LITERAL: Through him you have confidence in God, who raised him from the dead, and gave him glory, so that your faith and hope are in God.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Bosong bekin iko apa yang batúl. Jadi sakarang bosong bisa karjá ukur kuat kasi sang Tuhan. Itu bekin bosong sayang batúl sang bosong pung sodara orang parcaya dong. Bosong pung sayang tu musti batamba kuat, tagal bosong pung hati barisi.<bt>You do according to/obey what is true. So (consequently) now you can work your guts out (idiom: measuring strength) for God2. That makes you really love your sibling believers. That love of your must increase in strength, because of your clean/pure/holy livers. [EXEG: The cause-effect indicated by Gk /en/ broadly ‘in’, but here more commonly translated as ‘through’, has to be turned on its head in these RL lgs, hence the “obedience to the truth” coming first. The effect of the Gk participle “having been purified” is handled by the higher level clause relations. “soul” is a squishy concept in these lgs, and overlaps very clearly with the concept of “insides” (which Fox, myself, Barbara, van Klinken, and others have published on).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hagnizw: purify anupokritos: genuine, sincere|i(22) (22)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">hagnizw: purify anupokritos: genuine, sincere<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>ektenws: earnestly, deeply LITERAL: Having purified your souls by your obedience to the truth, for a sincere love of the brothers, love one another earnestly from the heart.<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Sakarang bosong su dapa idop baru. Ma ini idop baru ni, bosong sonde dapa dari bosong pung mama-bapa yang nanti mati di ini dunya, ma bosong dapa dari kotong pung Bapa di sorga yang sonde tau mati. Bosong pung idop baru ni, bosong dapa lewat Tuhan pung Kata-kata. Dia pung Kata-kata ni, ada bawa idop yang batúl, deng ada batahan tarús.<bt>Now you have gotten/obtained new life. But this new life now, your did not get from you mother-father in this world who will later die, but you god from our-inc Father in heaven who cannot die. This new life of your, you got by/via God2's Words/Message. These Words/Message of His, bring real life, and continue to endure/persevere. [EXEG: NLT, Message, Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV badly undertranslated ; ***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">!@ CEV badly undertranslated ; *** (2009) changed place of modifier “yang nanti mati” so modifies parents, not world.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Here &quot;living word of God&quot; associates"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">Here "living word of God" associates the Word and life, not God and life, though both are true. LITERAL: You have been born anew, not of perishable seed, but of imperishable, through the living and abiding word of God<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Te Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the *Scriptures (God2's Holy Writings) write saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Manusia sama ke satu rumput, ko, satu bunga.<bt>“Humans are like a (blade of) grass, or, a flower.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ato = mesolectal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">ato = mesolectal</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te dong pung bagus tu, sonde batahan tarús.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) their beauty will not endure on continually. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Rumput, layu buang.<bt>Grass withers away.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bunga ju, gugur buang.<bt>Flowers also (petals) fall off completely.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Lai sadiki dong mati, ais ilang buang.<bt>Soon they die, and then disappear.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: For, &quot;All flesh is like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: For, "All flesh is like grass, and all its glory like the flower of grass. The grass withers and the flower falls,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="25" />Ma kotong pung Bos pung Kata-kata,<bt>But our-inc Bos's Words/Message,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">batahan tarús, deng sonde tau putus-putus.&gt;&gt;<bt>keeps on enduring/persevering, and never ends.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, Tuhan pung Kata-kata dong tu, andia itu Kabar Bae yang botong su kasi tau sang bosong.<bt>Naa, [+shift, comment] those Words/Message of God2's, that is the Good News which we-exc have told you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rheema: particularizes the Gospel to what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">rheema: particularizes the Gospel to what was actually said, rather than the Gospel idea in general LITERAL: But the word of the Lord lasts forever." That word is the good news which was preached to you.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:24-25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:6-8</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong jadi Tuhan pung orang barisi<bt>We-inc are God2's clean/holy/pure people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi bosong jang bekin jahat apa-apa. Jang maen paricuk deng orang. Jang muka-balakang. Jang iri hati. Jang omong bekin busuk orang pung nama bae. Angka buang itu samua su!<bt>So (consequently) you should not do any evil. Don't go around deceiving/dealing dishonestly with people. Don't front-back (=say one thing and do another). Don't be jealous/hateful. Don't speak to ruin other people's good name/reputation. Get rid of all those things!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maen panake = UNS not know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">maen panake = UNS not know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apothew: lay aside, put away, rid"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">apothew: lay aside, put away, rid yourself of, get rid of kakia: evil, malice, wickedness, opposite of virtue<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>dolos: deceit, cunning, treachery, guile hupokrisis: hypocrisy, insincerity<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>phthonos: envy, jealousy katalalia: slander, defamation, evil speech<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERAL: Therefore get rid of all wickedness, and all deceit, and insincerity, and jealousy, and all slander.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ana mea dong rindu mau minum aer susu dari dong pung mama. Bagitu ju, bosong pung hati musti rindu mau mangarti Tuhan pung Kata-kata. Te itu yang bekin bosong pung parcaya tamba hari tamba kuat. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa batumbu jadi dewasa yang idop iko Tuhan pung mau.<bt>Infants yearn to drink their mother's milk. In the same way, your livers must yearn to understand God's Words/Message. Cuz (elaboration) that is what makes your faith keep growing stronger daily. In that way, you can grow to become an adult/mature, who lives according to God2's will. [EXEG: Ex. Summ #2 on “spiritual milk”, and #1 on “grow up to salvation”. NLT grow into the fullness of your salvation. IVP progress toward the goal of complete deliverance from sin and increasing in love; TG spiritual maturity which is a result of the growth process; Uma BT your spiritual life [lit., life of your soul] will grow stronger-and-stronger and more-and-more-mature/clear.] [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT (rindu): Ana mea dong cari mama pung susu. Bagitu ju, bosong musti cari Tuhan pung Kata-kata. Te itu Kata-kata dong bekin bosong pung parcaya tamba hari tamba kuat.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="artigennetos: new born brephos: infant|i(2) (2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">artigennetos: new born brephos: infant<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>logikos: reasonable, rational, spiritual [not physical] adolos: pure, unadulterated, without deceit<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>gala: milk epipothew: desire, long for, crave<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>auksanw: grow, increase LITERAL: Like newborn babies long for the pure spiritual milk, that by it you may grow up to salvation.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng bagitu, bosong bisa batumbu jadi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Deng bagitu, bosong bisa batumbu jadi dewasa, ko Tuhan kasi salamat sang bosong dari bosong pung sala. // rindu mau dapa hal yang bae dari Tuhan. Deng bagitu, waktu bosong su batumbu jadi dewasa, Tuhan su kasi salamat sang bosong dari bosong pung sala.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te bosong su rasa ame kotong pung Bos pung hati bae.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you have tasted/felt/experienced our-inc Bos's goodness/grace/kindness/generosity.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="geuomai: come to know something, experience"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">geuomai: come to know something, experience something, taste xrestos: kind, loving, benevolent<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERAL: If you have experienced that the Lord is kind.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 34:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ika diri deng Kristus. Te Dia sama ke satu batu, ma Dia ada pung idop. Tukang dong su angka buang itu batu, tagal dong pikir bilang, itu batu sonde ada pung guna. Ma Tuhan Allah anggap Dia pung harga talalu mahal, ais su pili ame sang Dia, ko jadi batu alas yang paling pantíng.<bt>Bind/tie/link yourselves to Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) He is like a stone/rock, but/except He has life. The craftsmen have picked up thrown away that stone, because they thought that stone has no use. But God viewed/considered His/Its worth/value to be too great/expensive, and so has chosen/selected/set aside Him/It, to be the most important base/undergirding stone. [NOTE: METAPHOR: at consultant check 2/3 UNS's drew a blank on “living stone”. Hence, current adjustment.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ He is like a stone,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">@@ He is like a stone, but/except that He has life. @@ 2/3 of the UNS's didn't get it.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proserxomai: approach, come to lithos: stone|i(4)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">proserxomai: approach, come to lithos: stone<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>zaw: live apodokimazw: reject, declare useless, repudiate after a test, disallow<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>eklektos: chosen, picked, select, choice entimos: honored, precious, prized, prized<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERAL: Come to him, to that living stone, rejected by men, but in God's sight, chosen and precious.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ika diri deng Kristus. Te Dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Ika diri deng Kristus. Te Dia sama ke satu batu alas yang tukang dong su tola buang. Ma Tuhan Allah anggap Dia pung harga talalu mahal, ais su pili ame sang Dia. Ma Dia bukan batu biasa sa, te Dia sama ke batu yang ada pung idop. Te Dia sama ke satu batu yang ada pung idop.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Bosong ju musti ta'ika deng Kristus, ko biar Tuhan Allah ju pake sang bosong. Deng bagitu, bosong sama ke batu yang Tuhan pili ame ko bangun ruma kasi Dia pung Roh. Bosong ju sama ke batu yang ada pung idop, sama ke Kristus. Bosong sama ke kapala agama dong, yang idop barisi kasi sang Tuhan. Itu sama ke bosong ada bawa korban kasi sang Dia. Bosong pung korban dong bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati, tagal Yesus Kristus su mati kasi sang bosong samua.<bt>You-pl must also be bound/linked with Kristus, so that God will also use you. In that way, you are like a stone that God2 chose/selected/set aside to build a house/building for His Spirit. You are also like stones that have life, just like Kristus. You are like *priests (heads of religion) who live clean/holy/pure for God2. That is like you are bringing *sacrifices to Him. Your sacrifices please God2's liver, because Yesus Kristus has (already) died for all of you. [EXEG: “spiritual sacrifices” undertranslated as in CEV, taken as indicating the acceptability of the sacrifices as per Ex.Summ. #2.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oikodomew: build pneumatikos: spiritual|i(5) (5) |rhierateuma:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">oikodomew: build pneumatikos: spiritual<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>hierateuma: priesthood hagios: holy<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>anapherw: offer up thusia: sacrifice<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>euprosdektos: acceptable LITERAL: And like living stones, be yourselves built into a spiritual house, to be a holy priesthood, to offer spiritual sacrifices, acceptable to God through Jesus Christ.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Te ada tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it is written in the Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lia dolo! Te Beta ada taro batu partama,<bt>“Look here/there! Cuz (elaboration) I have put/placed/laid the first stone,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">di kota Yerusalem sini,<bt>here in the city of Yerusalem,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang dong subu bilang, &lt;kota Sion&gt;.<bt>which they refer to as ‘city of Sion’.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta yang su pili ame itu batu.<bt>I am the one who chose/selected that stone.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung harga mahal kasi sang Beta.<bt>It's price/value is expensive/valuable to Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Jadi orang yang parcaya sang Dia,<bt>So (consequently), a person who believes in Him/It,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti sonde dapa malu apa-apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later will not be ashamed/embarrassed at all/in any way.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="periexw: stand tithemi: put|i(6) (6) |rakrogwniaios:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">periexw: stand tithemi: put<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>akrogwniaios: cornerstone kataisxunw: disappoint<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>Partial parallels in Matthew 21:42, Mark 12:10, Luke 20:17, and Acts 4:11 just go up to "corner block", not anything about God's or people's reaction to it. LITERAL: For it stands in Scripture, "Behold, I am laying in Zion a stone, a cornerstone, chosen and precious, and he who believes in him will not be disappointed/put to shame."<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 28:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Yesus sama ke itu batu. Ais, kasi orang yang parcaya sang Dia, Dia pung harga ju mahal. Ma kasi orang yang sonde parcaya sang Dia, Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang,<bt>Yesus is like that stone. So then, to people who believe in Him, His price/value is expensive/valuable. But to people who don't believe in Him, the Scriptures write saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Itu batu yang tukang dong su angka buang,<bt>“That stone that the craftsmen have picked up thrown away,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sakarang su jadi batu partama,<bt>now has already become the first stone,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang paling pantíng.&gt;&gt;<bt>which is the most important.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apodokimaxw: declare useless gnwnia: corner|i(7) (7)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">apodokimaxw: declare useless gnwnia: corner<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERAL: Therefore, to you who believe, he is precious. But for those who do not believe, "The stone which the builders rejected, that one has become the head of the corner."</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ada tatulis lai bilang,<bt>It is also written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ada batu yang bekin orang ta'antok.<bt>“There is a stone which makes/causes people to stumble.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ada batu yang bekin dong jato.&gt;&gt;<bt>there is a rock that makes them fall.”</bt><note reference="2:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 8:14-15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, dong jato tagal dong sonde mau bekin iko Tuhan pung Kata-kata. Te Tuhan su ator memang ko dong jato bagitu.<bt>Naa, [+shift] they fall because they don't want to do according to /obey God2's Words/Message. Cuz (elaboration) God2 has arranged/set things up/organised beforehand for them to fall like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proskomma: stumble, trip skandalon: trap, temptation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">proskomma: stumble, trip skandalon: trap, temptation to sin, enticement<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>proskoptw: take offense apeithew: disobey<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>tithemi: make someone something, destine, appoint someone for something LITERAL: and "A stone that will make men stumble, a rock that will make them fall", for they stumble because they disobey the word, as they were destined to do.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma bosong sonde bagitu. Te bosong jadi orang yang Tuhan Allah su pili sandiri. Bosong jadi Dia pung milik. Bosong sama ke kapala agama yang layani sang raja. Bosong ju sama ke satu bangsa yang idop barisi kasi sang Tuhan. Bosong jadi bagitu, ko biar bosong bisa kasi tau samua orang so'al Tuhan Allah pung hati bae, yang Dia bekin kasi sang bosong. Te Dia su suru bosong kasi tenga hal jahat, ko idop deng bekin yang bae. Itu sama ke bosong kaluar dari galáp, ko idop di Dia pung taráng yang bagus talalu.<bt>But you-pl are not like that. Cuz (elaboration) you are people whom God has chosen/selected/set aside himself/personally. You are His possession. You are like priests who serve/minister to the king. You are also like a nation/people group who lives clean/pure/holy for God2. You are like that, so that you can tell/explain to everyone about God's goodness/grace/kindness/generosity, that He has done for you. Cuz (elaboration) He has ordered/commanded you to leave behind/abandon evil things, to live doing what is good. That is like you have come out of the dark, to live in His light that is so magnificant/beautiful.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bagus &gt; talalu bagus &gt; bagus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">bagus &gt; talalu bagus &gt; bagus talalu (negative, superlative) @@</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="genos: nation, people, race peripoiesis: possession,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">genos: nation, people, race peripoiesis: possession, property, keeping safe, belong to<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>arete: praise, virtue, excellence eksaggellw: proclaim, declare, tell out, make known<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>thaumastos: wonderful, marvelous LITERAL: But you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, God's possession, that you may make known the wonderful deeds of him who called you out of darkness into his marvelous light.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 19:5-6, Yesaya 43:20. 21, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 4:20, 7:6, 14:2, Titus 2:14, Yesaya 9:2</note><v n="10" />Dolu bosong jadi sama ke satu kelu yang sonde ada pung arti apa-apa. Ma sakarang bosong su maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung kelu. Dolu bosong sonde mau tarima Tuhan pung rasa kasian sang bosong. Ma sakarang bosong su tarima ame.<bt>Previously you-pl were like a family that had no significance at all. But now you have entered to become God's family. Previously you didn't want to receive/accept God2's mercy/pity for you. But now you have received/accepted it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: Once you were no people,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: Once you were no people, but now you are God's people. Once you had not received mercy, but now you have received mercy.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dolu, Tuhan mau kasi tunju Dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Dolu, Tuhan mau kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang bosong, ma bosong sonde mau tarima. Ais, sakarang, baru bosong tarima.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 2:23</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jaga bae-bae ko kotong idop batúl<bt>Guard carefully so that we-inc live right/correct/true</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sodara sayang dong! Bosong ni, cuma jadi tamu di ini dunya sa. Te bosong sama ke orang asing yang ada maranto. Andia ko beta maen minta ko bosong jang sama ke manusia laen di ini dunya, yang bekin jahat iko dong pung mau-mau. Te dalam bosong pung hati ada satu paráng. Andia, kapingin bekin jahat baparáng lawan kapingin bekin bae. Jadi, jang kasi biar itu kapingin bekin jahat ontong ame sang bosong. Te kalo bagitu, na, bosong ancor!<bt>Dear siblings! You-pl here are only/merely guests/visitors in this world. Cuz (elaboration) you are like foreigners who are living abroad. That is why I keep requesting that you not be the same as other humans in this world, who do evil according to their desires/whims/passions. Cuz (elaboration) inside your livers there is a war/battle. that is, the desire to do evil is at war opposing the desire to do good. So (consequently), don't allow that desire to do evil to gain advantage/profit/win/beat you. Cuz (elaboration) if it's like that, you're ruined/destroyed/things fall apart!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manáng = win, focuses on final"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">manáng = win, focuses on final state ; ontong = gain benefit, advantage (process, incipient state onwards)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paroikos: stranger, alien, foreigner parepidemos: exile,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">paroikos: stranger, alien, foreigner parepidemos: exile, refugee, temporary resident<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>apexw: abstain, keep away epithumia: desire, longing<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>strateuw: do military service. Romans 7:23 psuxe: soul, life, seat and center of life that goes beyond the earthly<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERAL: Beloved, I appeal to you, as aliens and exiles, to abstain from the passions of the flesh that wage war against your soul.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sodara sayang dong! Di ini dunya,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Sodara sayang dong! Di ini dunya, bosong cuma jadi tamu sa. Bosong sama ke orang asing yang maranto di sini sa. Andia ko beta maen minta tarús ko bosong jang bekin jahat iko bosong pung mau-mau sa, sama ke manusia biasa. Te dalam bosong pung hati ada kapingin bekin jahat yang baparáng lawan kapingin bekin bae (ko mau bekin rusak sang bosong). Jang kasi biar itu kapingin bekin jahat ontong di/sang bosong!</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Jaga bae-bae ko bosong idop batúl di muka orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan. Deng bagitu, andekata dong mau tudu bosong sambarang, na, dong cuma dapa lia bosong pung bae sa. Ais kalo Kristus datang kambali, dong sandiri yang nanti angka tinggi-tinggi sang Tuhan Allah, tagal bosong pung bekin bae.<bt>Guard carefully so you live right/correctly in front of people who don't know/recognise God2. In that way, if perchance (hypothetical) they were going to accuse you arbitrarily/anyway/recklessly, na, they would only be able to see your good. So/then, if/when Kristus comes back, they themselves are the ones who will *glorify (elevate way up high) God, because of your good deeds.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anastrophe: conduct, way of life, behavior"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">anastrophe: conduct, way of life, behavior epopteuw: observe, see, watch<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>episkope: visitation LITERAL: Have good conduct among the nations/Gentiles, so that in case they speak against you as wrongdoers, they may see your good deeds, and glorify God on the day of [God's] visitation.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jaga bae-bae bosong pung peri laku"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Jaga bae-bae bosong pung peri laku kalu bosong ada bakumpul deng orang yang balóm dapa salamat dong. Biarpun itu waktu dong curiga deng lawan sang bosong, ma nanti waktu Kristus kambali, dong nanti puji sang Tuhan Allah tagal apa yang bae yang bosong bekin.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong musti dengar-dengar sang orang yang pegang kuasa<bt>We-inc must keep listening to/obeying people who hold power/authority</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Kotong pung Bos pung mau ko bosong dengar-dengar sang samua orang yang pegang kuasa. Conto ke: dengar-dengar sang raja, te dia jadi pamimpin yang tinggi.<bt>Our-inc Bos desires for you to keep listening to/obeying everyone who holds power/authority. For example: keep listening to/obeying the king, cuz (elaboration) he is the highest leader.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupotassw: subject oneself, subordinate oneself, obey,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">hupotassw: subject oneself, subordinate oneself, obey, be submissive ktisis: institution, social structure, authority, every person who has a right to rule<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERAL: Be subject to every human institution for the Lord's sake, whether it be to the emperor/king as supreme,</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Dengar-dengar sang gubernor, te raja su utus sang dia, ko dia kasi jato hukuman sang orang yang bekin jahat dong, deng dia angka puji sang orang yang bekin hal yang batúl dong.<bt>Keep listening to/obeying the gubernor, cuz (elaboration) the king has sent/commissioned him so he will hand down punishment to people who do evil, and he will lift up praise for people who do what is right/correct.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hegemwn: governor, leader, president, proconsul, chief"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">hegemwn: governor, leader, president, proconsul, chief magistrate epainon: praise, approval, recognition, commend, reward<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERAL: or to governors as sent by him to punish those who do wrong, and to praise those who do right.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Andia ko Tuhan Allah suka ko bosong bekin yang batúl dong, ko biar orang bodo yang sonde tau apa-apa, sonde ada alasan ko tudu ame sang bosong.<bt>That is why God likes for you to do what is right/correct/ture, so that stupid/ignorant people who don't know anything, won't have a reason/basis/excuse for accusing you (successfully).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phimow: tie up, tie shut, muzzle,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">phimow: tie up, tie shut, muzzle, put to silence aphrwn: foolish, ignorant, lack of insight, thoughtless, senseless<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>agnwsia: ignorance, [not intellectually but in religious experience] LITERAL: Because that way it is God's will that by doing good you should put to silence the ignorance of foolish men.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Biar bosong jadi orang bebas yang ada pung hak ko bekin iko bosong pung suka, ma jang pake sambarang itu hak ko bekin hal yang jahat. Pake itu hak ko karjá kasi sang Tuhan, te bosong jadi Dia pung milik.<bt>Even if/though you are free people who have the right to do whatever you like, nevertheless don't arbitrarily/thoughtlessly/recklessly/pointlessly use that right to do evil things. Use that right to work for God2, cuz (elaboration) your are His possession.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eleutheros: free [in the religious and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">eleutheros: free [in the religious and moral sense] as in 1 Corinthians 9:1 epikalumma: cover, veil<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERAL: As free men, yet without using your freedom as a pretext for evil, but as servants of God.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Bosong musti taro hormat sang samua orang. Bosong musti sayang sang samua orang yang parcaya sang Kristus. Bosong musti idop pantas di Tuhan pung muka, te nanti Dia yang putus hukuman kasi bosong. Deng bosong musti taro hormat sang dong yang pegang parenta.<bt>You must place respect/honour for all people. You must love everyone who believes in Kristus. You must live appropriately before God2, cuz (elaboration) He is the one who will decide your punishment. And you must place respect/honour for those who hold government/rule.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="timaw: honor adelphotes: brotherhood, community of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">timaw: honor adelphotes: brotherhood, community of brothers<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>phobew: have reverence, respect, be afraid [in the sense of reverence] LITERAL: Honor all men, love the brotherhood, have reverence for God, honor the king/emperor.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong musti batahan dalam susa, iko Kristus pung conto<bt>We-inc must endure/persevere in trouble/difficulty, following Kristus' example</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Orang suru-suru dong! Dengar-dengar sang bosong pung bos dong, deng taro hormat sang dong. Jang cuma dengar-dengar sang bos yang hati bae deng manis sa. Ma andekata bosong pung bos jahat talalu, na, bosong musti dengar-dengar sang dia ju.<bt>Servants! Keep listening to/obeying your-pl bosses, and place respect/honour on them. Don't just keep listening to/obeying only the boss who is good and kind. But if perchance (hypothetical) your boss is excessively evil, na, you must keep listening to/obeying him too.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oiketai: member of the household, house"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">oiketai: member of the household, house slave, servant hupotassw: subject, submit, obey, be subordinated<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>phobos: reverence, respect, fear despotais: master<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>agathos: good [especially in the moral sense], benevolent epieikes: gentle, yielding, kind, considerate, fair, reasonable<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>skolios: crooked, unscrupulous, dishonest, harsh, unjust overbearing LITERAL: Servants, be submissive with all respect, not only to the good and gentle, but also to the harsh.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Kalo ada di bosong yang kaná hukum sambarang dari bosong pung bos biar bosong sonde bekin sala apa-apa, deng kalo bosong batahan dalam itu susa tagal bosong ada inga Tuhan pung mau kasi sang bosong, na, nanti Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong.<bt>If there are those of you who are punished arbitrarily/baselessly from/by your boos even though you have not done anything wrong, and if you endure/persevere in that trouble/difficulty because you are remembering God2's will for you, na, later God will show His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you. [EXEG: Uma BT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xaris: favor, grace, gracious care, gracious"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">xaris: favor, grace, gracious care, gracious help, goodwill suneidesis: consciousness, conscience, mindful, aware, conscience<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>hupopherw: bear uup under, endure, submit to lupe: grief, sorrow, pain [of mind or spirit]<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>pasxw: suffer, endure adikws: unjustly, undeservedly, wrongfully, unearned<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERAL: For one is approved if he endures pain while suffering unjustly, conscious of God.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Andekata bosong ada bekin sala, ais kaná pukul, na, dia pung ontong apa, kalo bosong batahan dalam itu susa? Sonde ada, to? Ma kalo bosong kaná susa tagal bosong bekin yang bae, ais bosong batahan, na, Tuhan ada taro hati sang bosong.<bt>If perchance you do wrong, and then get beaten, na, what gain/use/good/benefit is it if you endure in that difficulty? There is none, right? But if you are effected by difficulty/trouble because you do good, and then you endure/persevere, na, God2 is paying attention/looking after you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kleos: fame, glory, credit kolaphizw: strike"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">kleos: fame, glory, credit kolaphizw: strike with the fist, beat, cuff someone<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>hupomenw: remain, endure, hold out [in trouble, affliction, persecution] LITERAL: For what credit is it, if when you do wrong and are beaten for it, you take it patiently? But if when you do right and suffer for it, you take it patiently, you have God's approval.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo bosong ada bekin sala, ais"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Kalo bosong ada bekin sala, ais kaná pukul, ju bosong batahan bagitu, na, bosong dapa ontong apa?</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Te Kristus ju kapingin ko bosong idop bekin yang batúl, biar bosong kaná susa. Te Dia ju pikol susa kasi sang kotong. Deng bagitu, Dia jadi conto, ko kotong iko sang Dia, sama ke kotong ada jalan iko Dia pung bakás kaki.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) Kristus also desires for you to live doing what is right/correct, even if/though you experience trouble/difficulty. Cuz (elaboration) He also carried/bore difficulty/trouble for us-inc. In that way, He is/became an example. so we-inc follow Him, as if we are walking following/stepping in His footprints. [DISCOURSE: Shift from 2s - 1pi for genre reasons.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Poetry? hupolimpanw: leave, leave something behind"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">Poetry? hupolimpanw: leave, leave something behind for someone<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>hupogrammos: pattern, example, model ixnesis: footprint<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>LITERAL: For to this you have been called, because Christ also suffered for you, leaving you an example, that you should follow in his steps.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang,<bt>The Scriptures write saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dia sonde parná bekin sala.<bt>“He never did wrong/sin.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada putar-balek yang kaluar dari Dia pung mulu.&gt;&gt;<bt>There is no deceit that came out from His mouth.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dolos: deceit, guile, cunning, treachery, hypocrisy,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">dolos: deceit, guile, cunning, treachery, hypocrisy, insincerity, perjury LITERAL: He committed no sin, no deceit was found on his lips<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Waktu dong omong bekin hina sang Dia, Dia sonde balas. Waktu Dia kaná susa, Dia sonde ancam mau balas. Ma Dia sarakan Dia pung diri pi Tuhan Allah pung tangan. Te Dia parcaya bilang, Tuhan tu, Tukang Putus Parkara yang adil.<bt>When they spoke despising/insulting Him, He did not respond/retort. When He experienced trouble/difficulty, He did not threaten to repay. But He surrendered/turned over Himself into God's hands. Cuz (elaboration) He believed that God2 is a/the just/fair Judge.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="loidorew: revile, abuse, say harsh words,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">loidorew: revile, abuse, say harsh words, insult anteloidorew: revile in return, insult back, return an insult<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>epeilew: threaten, warn paradidwmi: give over, entrust something to someone, commit something to<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>LITERAL: When he was insulted, he did not insult in return. When he suffered, he did not threaten, but he entrusted himself to him who judges justly.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:7</note><v n="24" />Kristus tu, yang pikol kotong pung sala waktu Dia mati di kayu palang. Dia bekin bagitu, ko biar kotong sonde usa idop deng bekin sala lai. Ais sakarang kotong sonde idop deng bekin sala, ma kotong cuma idop deng bekin yang batúl sa. Te Dia su ganti ame sang kotong, ko tarima ame kotong pung hukuman. Itu hukuman bekin Dia luka-luka, sampe Dia mati. Te itu luka yang bekin Dia mati tu, su bekin bae sang bosong.<bt>Kristus is the one who carried our-inc wrongs/sin when He died on the *cross. He did that, so that we did not need to live doing wrong anymore. So now we don't live doing wrong, but we only live doing what is right/correct. Cuz (elaboration) He replaced us, to receive/accept our punishment. That punishment made Him full of wounds, to the point that He died. Cuz (elaboration) those wounds that made Him die, have healed you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anapherw: bring up, take up, bear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">anapherw: bring up, take up, bear up, offer up ksulon: cross<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>apoginomai: die [opposite of ginomai, 'to come into being'] mwlwps: wound, bruise, [caused by blows]<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>iaomai: heal, cure LITERAL: He himself bore our sins in his body on the tree, that we might die to sin and live to righteousness. By his wounds you have been healed.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:6</note><v n="25" />Te bosong sama ke domba yang dolu su jalan serong. Ma sakarang bosong su kambali pi Tuhan pung jalan lurus. Te Dia yang jaga deng piara bae-bae sang bosong, sama ke satu gambala yang jaga deng piara dia pung domba dong.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you are like sheep who previously deviated from the path. But now you have returned to God2's straight path. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who guards and cares for you well, like a shepherd who guards and cares for his sheep.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jalan serong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">jalan serong</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="planaw: stray, go astray, wander around,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">planaw: stray, go astray, wander around, be misled epistrephw: turn, return<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>poimen: shepherd episkopos: overseer, guardian<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>LITERAL: For you were straying like sheep, but have now returned to the Shepherd and Guardian of your souls.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nasiat kasi laki-bini dong<bt>Advice to husbands-wives</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Bini dong! Tadi beta bilang kotong musti dengar-dengar sang orang yang pegang kuasa. Jadi bosong musti dengar-dengar sang bosong pung laki. Inga te ada laki saparu yang sonde mau bekin iko Tuhan pung Kata-kata. Biar dong sonde mau dengar bosong pung kata-kata, ma dong nanti mau parcaya sang Kristus, tagal bosong pung idop.<bt>Wives! Earlier I said we-inc must keep listening to/obeying people who hold power/authority. So (consequently), you-pl must keep listening to/obeying your husbands. Keep in mind that there are some husbands who don't want to do according to /obey2 God2's Words/Message. Even thought ey don't want to listen to your words/message, nevertheless they are going to believe in Kristus, because of your lives. [EXEG: first sentence explicating “likewise”, from higher level context. NOTE to daughter translations: cohesion with 2:13. Play on words, be careful that first “dengar” in last sentence is constructed to force sense of “listen to”, not “obey”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="homoiws: likewise, similarly, in the same"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">homoiws: likewise, similarly, in the same way, in like manner [connects to 2:13] hupotassw: subject oneself, be subjected, be subordinated, obey, submit<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>apeithew: disobey, be disobedient, set self against the truth, oppose, willful refusal to submit [a strong word] anew: without<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>kerdainw: to gain, gain someone, be won, be converted anastrophe: way of life, conduct, behavior, deportment, manner of life<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERAL: Likewise wives, be submissive to your own husbands, so that some, though they do not obey the word, may be won without a word by the behavior of their wives.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te, andekata ada laki saparu yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Te, andekata ada laki saparu yang sonde mau bekin iko Tuhan pung Kata-kata, dong nanti mau parcaya sang Dia tagal bosong pung idop. biar sakarang dong sonde mau dengar bosong pung kata-kata.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 5:22, Kolose 3:18</note><v n="2" />Te dong lia, bosong ada bekin samua-samua deng hati yang lurus deng barisi di Tuhan Allah pung muka.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) they see you are doing everything with livers that are straight/righteous and clean/pure/holy before God. [NOTE to daughter translation: KM /hati lurus/ is a bit too broad for the sense of ‘reverent, godly behaviour’. See if you can find something closer, like /idop kasi tunju hormat sang TA/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epopteuw: observe, see something, watch phobos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">epopteuw: observe, see something, watch phobos: reverence, respect, fear, awe [of God]<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>hagnos: pure, holy, godly purity LITERAL: when they see your reverent, pure behavior.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Parampuan pung manis, bukan dari apa yang kantara dari luar. Conto ke: bagaya bekin rambu deng model macam-macam, ko, bastél lebe-lebe pake mas-perak, ko, pake pakean mahal-mahal yang sonde sopan.<bt>A woman's beauty (sweetness) is not from what is visible/evident from outside. For example: fashionable hair-does of various sorts, or, over-dressing with gold-silver, or, wearing really expensive clothes that are not polite/decent. [NOTE to daughter translations: compare wording in 1 Tim. 2:9-10.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rambut pata mayang = ?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">rambut pata mayang = ?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="1 Tim 2:9-10 (KM): Bagitu ju"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">1 Tim 2:9-10 (KM): Bagitu ju deng parampuan dong. Beta mau ko dong ator diri yang pantas, deng pake pakean yang sopan. Sonde usa bagaya ko bekin orang pasang mata sang dong, deng pake model rambut macam-macam, ko pake pakean mahal-mahal yang sonde sopan, ko bastél lebe-lebe pake mas-perak deng mutiara dong. Te yang bekin parampuan dong jadi manis tu, andia dong pung hati yang barisi, deng dong salalu bekin yang bae. Itu yang pantas kasi parampuan yang semba sang Tuhan Allah.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: Let not yours be the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: Let not yours be the outward adorning, with braiding of hair, decoration of gold, and wearing of robes,</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Timotius 2:9-10</note><v n="4" />Ma yang bekin parampuan dong jadi manis batúl, andia: dong pung hati yang sonde kantara dari luar. Conto ke: hati manis, deng kalam. Te manis macam bagitu tu, sonde ilang buang, biar parampuan su jadi tua. Iko Tuhan pung nilei, manis macam bagitu tu, dia pung harga mahal.<bt>But what makes a woman really pretty/beautiful is this: their livers/character that is not visible/evident from outside. For example: livers that are kind and calm/gentle/stable. Cuz (elaboration) beauty of that sort, does not disappear, even though a woman is already old. According to God2's assessment, beauty of that sort is very valuable.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kruptos: hidden, secret aphthartw: imperishable, incorruptible,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">kruptos: hidden, secret aphthartw: imperishable, incorruptible, unfading, ageless, lasting<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>praus: gentle, humble, considerate, meek, unassuming, unprovoking hesuxios: quiet, calm, sweet<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>pneuma: spirit, disposition, spiritual state, state of mind poluteles: costly, precious, of great price, very valuable<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERAL: but the hidden person of the heart, with the imperishable beauty of a gentle and quiet spirit [/disposition], which in God's sight is very precious.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Te dolu-dolu, parampuan yang hati barisi dong, yang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, dong pung manis ju bagitu. Dong ju dengar-dengar sang dong pung laki.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) long ago, those women who had clean/pure/holy livers, who believed in God, their beauty was also like that. They also kept listening to/obeying their husbands.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: For so once the holy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: For so once the holy women who hoped in God used to adorn themselves, and were submissive to their own husbands,</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ame conto dari nene Sara. Dia dengar-dengar sang dia pung laki Abraham. Dia ju kasi biar dia pung laki ator sang dia. Bosong parampuan ju musti iko dia pung model, deng cara bosong bekin yang batúl, ais sonde taku apa-apa ju.<bt>Take the example of grandmother Sara. She kept listening to/obeying her husband Abraham. She also allowed her husband to oversee/arrange her. You women must also follow her type/kind/model, by means of doing what is right/correct, and also not fearing anything. [EXEG: Connectors in last sentence fixed from earlier version to better reflect the Gk.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupakouw: obey phobos: fear, reverence, respect|i(6)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">hupakouw: obey phobos: fear, reverence, respect<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>medeis: no ptoesis: fear, terror, sudden fear, trepidation, scare<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERAL: as Sarah obeyed Abraham, calling him "lord". And you are her children, doing right and not fearing any terror [/do not give way to fear].</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 18:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Laki dong! Idop satu hati deng bosong pung bini. Timbang bae-bae apa yang bae kasi sang dia, ais bekin iko. Kasi tunju hormat sang dia dalam samua hal, tagal parampuan pung kuat sonde sama ke laki-laki pung kuat. Te bosong sama-sama tarima ame pusaka yang Tuhan Allah mau kasi sang bosong. Andia, sama-sama tarima idop baru yang Tuhan kasi sang bosong dari Dia pung hati bae. Ma bosong laki dong musti idop satu hati deng bosong pung bini bagitu, ko biar kalo bosong dua ada angka hati ko sambayang minta satu hal dari Tuhan, na, Dia mau dengar sang bosong.<bt>Husbands! Live one livered (united, one accord, same purpose) with your wives. Weigh/assess carefully what is good for her, and then do accordingly. Show respect/honour to her in everything, because women's strength is not the same as men's strength. Cuz (elaboration) together/the same you received the inheritance that God wants/is going to give you. That is, together (you) received new life which God2 gave to you from His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity. But you husbands must live one livered with your wives like that, so that if the two of you are lifting your livers to pray requesting something from God2, na, He will want to listen to you. [EXEG: NLT; The trick is to reflect physical asymmetry, and a spiritual standing/heritage of symmetry (co-heirs).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note expanded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) note expanded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skeuos: vessel sugkleronomos: joint heirs, co-heirs|i(7)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">skeuos: vessel sugkleronomos: joint heirs, co-heirs<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>egkoptew: hinder, thwart, blocked, made ineffective LITERAL: Likewise, the husbands, live with your wives considerately, bestowing honor on the woman as the weaker sex, since you are joint heirs of the grace of life, so that your prayers may not be hindered.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tagal parampuan sonde sama kuat ke/deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">tagal parampuan sonde sama kuat ke/deng laki-laki</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 5:25, Kolose 3:19</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Biar bosong bekin yang batúl, bosong nanti dapa susa ju<bt>Even if/though you-pl do what is right, you will still get trouble/difficulty</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Sodara sayang dong! Dia pung ahir, beta ada mau omong satu hal. Bosong samua ju musti idop satu hati. Kalo satu orang rasa susa ko sanáng, na, bosong yang laen ju musti iko rasa bagitu. Sayang sang orang yang parcaya sang Kristus dong. Kasi tunju hati manis satu deng satu. Jang angka-angka diri, te bosong musti randá hati.<bt>Dear siblings! Finally/in the end, I am wanting to say one (more) thing. All of you must also live one livered (united, one accord, same purpose). If/when one person is feeling troubled or happy, na, the others of you must also follow/participate feeling that. Love everyone who believes in Kristus. Show kindness/gentleness/sensitivity to each other. Don't lift yourselves up (proud), cuz you must be humble (idiom: low livered). [NOTE to daughter translations: “Finally” here is a high-level discourse structure marker. Trace the vocatives. “Beloved, I urge you...” (2:11) “Slaves, accept the authority...” (2:18) “Wives, in the same way, accept the authority...” (3:1) “Husbands, in the same way, show consideration...” (3:7) “Finally, all of you, have unity of spirit...” (3:8) But keep in mind that Peter continues talking for 2 more chapters. So CHECK if this will be taken as introducing a book-level closure, or the last in a list. If it's a problem, say “One more thing...” /Ada lagi satu hal.../.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="homophrwn: like minded, united in spirit,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">homophrwn: like minded, united in spirit, harmonious, agree sumpathes: sympathetic, compassionate, feeling for each other<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>philadelphos: loving one's brother eusplagkhnos: compassionate, tenderhearted, sensitive, affectionate<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>tapeinophronos: humble, modest, lowly-minded, self-effacing LITERAL: Finally, all of you, be like-minded, have sympathy, love of the brothers, a tender heart, a humble mind,<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Jang balas jahat deng jahat. Kalo orang maen karitik sang bosong, jang karitik bale sang itu orang. Ma minta ko Tuhan bekin yang bae kasi sang dia. Te Tuhan su pange ame sang bosong jadi Dia pung orang, ko biar bosong bisa tarima yang bae dari Dia.<bt>Don't repay evil with evil. If/when a person keeps criticising/find fault with you-pl, don't criticise that person back. And ask that God2 do what is good/beneficial for him/her. Cuz (elaboration) God2 has called you to be His people, so that you can receive what is good from Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="loidoria: verbal abuse, reproach, reviling, cursing,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">loidoria: verbal abuse, reproach, reviling, cursing, snap back, angry word LITERAL: Do not return evil for evil or reproach for reproach, but on the contrary, bless. For to this you have been called, that you may obtain a blessing.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te ada tatulis di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it is written in the Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Orang yang cari idop bae,<bt>“A person who seeks a good life, [NOTE to daughter translations: literal “idop sanáng” triggers a sense of selfish pursuit of pleasure, whereas both the context in Psalms and here it is intended as genuine “rules for good living”. Like the Gk, /idop bae/ is neutral. It can mean “good life” in its broadest sense, or it can be taken in a narrow (selfish) sense as “fat &amp; happy”. Avoid the latter. ALT: /idop yang bae/. If that doesn't work, try the less satisfactory and narrower /idop badame/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Orang yang cuma mau idop sanáng,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">&lt;&lt;Orang yang cuma mau idop sanáng,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) 1st two lines of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) 1st two lines of quote revised to fit better overall tone in context</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng yang cari idop panjang,<bt>and those who seek a long life,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) revised"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) revised</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko cuma mau idop ena-ena tiap"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">ko cuma mau idop ena-ena tiap hari sa,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">itu orang musti jaga dia pung mulu ko jang bagatal,<bt>that person must guard his mouth so it doesn't itch (idiom: gossip, rude), [NOTE to daughter translations: if /jaga mulu/ carries it, then /ko jang bagatal/ is optional.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng jang omong putar-balek.<bt>and not speak deceitfully.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: For, &quot;He that would love"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: For, "He that would love life, and see good days, let him keep his tongue from evil, and his lips from speaking deceit.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Dia musti tobat, ko jang bekin jahat lai,<bt>S/he must repent, to not do evil anymore,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma bale ko bekin yang batúl sa.<bt>but turn/change to just do what is right.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia musti balajar ko idop badame deng samua orang,<bt>S/he must learn to live in peace (relationships) with everyone,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ais cari jalan ko babae deng dong.<bt>and look for ways to be in right relationships with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: And let him turn away"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: And let him turn away from evil and do right, let him seek peace and pursue it</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="12" />Te yang hak parenta sang kotong ada taro mata<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the one who has the say-so/ordering rights over us-inc places eyes (idiom: watches over, takes care of)</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sang orang yang idop lurus.<bt>on people who live straight/righteous.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Dia ju mau dengar dong pung sambayang.<bt>And He also wants to listen to their prayers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma kotong pung Bos ada malawan tarús<bt>But our Bos keeps opposing</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sang orang yang idop bekin jahat.&gt;&gt;<bt>people who live doing evil.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cf below adjusted to include vs."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">cf below adjusted to include vs. 12</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: For the eyes of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: For the eyes of the Lord are upon the righteous, and his ears are open to their prayer. But the face of the Lord is against those that do evil."</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:10-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 34:12-17</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Kalo bosong samangat bekin yang batúl, sapa mau bekin jahat sang bosong lai? Sonde ada, to?<bt>If/when you are enthusiastic to do what is right, who is going to do evil to you? Nobody, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: And who will harm you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: And who will harm you if you are enthusiastic for what is right?</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ma biar bosong bekin yang batúl, ais ada yang bekin susa sang bosong, bosong ontong. Kalo ada orang yang sonde kanál sang Kristus jadi taku tagal satu hal, na, bosong jang iko jadi taku bagitu. Bosong pung pikiran jang kaco deng hati susa sama ke dong.<bt>But even if you do what is right, and then there are those who make/cause trouble/difficulty to you, you are fortunate. If there is a person who does not know/recognise Kristus (who) becomes afraid because of something, na, you should not follow in becoming afraid like that. Your thinking should not be chaotic/in disarray and liver troubled like them. [EXEG: NRSV “Do not fear what they fear and do not be intimidated.”; HCE “No scared da same tings dat scare dem, an no come all mix up.” Another Gk scholar (JEG) puts this combination as “Do not have fear of their terror, or be troubled.” ; EX.Summ. ties in to higher level issues and puts it “They are not to have the same fears as other people who don’t know Christ.” See also Gk notes below.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pahala = upa *** (2009) note"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">pahala = upa *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makarios: blessed, fortunate tarassw: be troubled,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">makarios: blessed, fortunate tarassw: be troubled, be frightened, be terrified, be intimidated, stir up, disturb, be unsettle, be confused<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERAL: But even if you suffer for righteousness, you are blessed. Do not have fear of their terror, or be troubled.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:10</note><v n="15" />Bekin bosong pung hati tanáng sa, tagal bosong su angka sang Kristus di bosong pung hati ko jadi bosong pung Bos yang barisi.<bt>Just make your livers calm, because you have elevated Kristus in your livers to be your Bos who is clean/pure/holy.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Andekata orang minta bosong ko kasi tau bosong pung parcaya, deng kanapa bosong ada baharap bilang, Kristus nanti bekin samua jadi bae, na, bosong musti siap sadia ko manyao sang dong.<bt>If perchance (hypothetical) a person requests you-pl to tell/explain your belief, and why you are hoping that Kristus will make everything become good, na, you must be prepared to respond/answer them. [NOTE to daughter translations: TB versification is off between v 15-16, if anyone is concerned.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hagiazw: sanctify, treat as holy, reverence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">hagiazw: sanctify, treat as holy, reverence LITERAL: But treat Christ as holy in your hearts. Always be ready to give an answer to everyone who asks you the reason for the hope that is in you.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:14-15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 8:12-13</note><v n="16" />Ma bosong musti manyao dari hati yang manis, deng kasi tunju hormat sang dong, ko biar dong tau bosong ada bekin yang batúl dari hati barisi. Biar bosong bekin yang bae bagitu, ma pasti ada yang mau omong kasi jato sang bosong, tagal bosong ada ta'ika deng Kristus. Jadi kalo bosong bekin yang bae tarús, na, dong yang olok-olok sang bosong nanti jadi malu.<bt>But you must respond from a kind/gentle/sensitive liver, and show respect for them, so that they know you are doing what is right from a clean/pure/holy liver. Even if you do what is right, nevertheless there will surely be those who speak to bring you down, because you are bound/linked with Kristus. So (consequently) if you keep doing what is good, na, those who scoff at/mock you will later be ashamed/embarrassed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katalalew: speak against, speak evil of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">katalalew: speak against, speak evil of epereaxw: threaten, mistreat, abuse, revile, use hard words, verbal abuse [stronger than katalalew]<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>kataisxunw: be put to shame, be humiliated LITERAL: Yet do it with gentleness and reverence, having a clear conscience, so that when you are spoken against, those who verbally abuse your good behavior in Christ may be put to shame.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Kalo itu iko Tuhan pung mau, na, jang lupa, te ada lebe bae bosong dapa susa tagal bekin yang batúl; jang tagal bosong ada bekin sala.<bt>If that is according to Gos2's will, na, don't forget that it is better that you get trouble/difficulty because of doing what is right; don't (get it) because you are doing wrong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: For it is better to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: For it is better to suffer for doing right, if that should be God's will, than for doing wrong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />Te Kristus mati satu kali,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) Kristus died one time,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal kotong manusia ada bekin sala.<bt>because we-inc humans were doing wrong/sin.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia yang idop lurus,<bt>He who lived straight/righteous,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">su mati kasi sang kotong yang idop kamomos.<bt>has died for us-inc who lived filthy/defiled.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia mati ko biar bosong bisa babae kambali deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>He died so the you could be retored to a right relationship with God. [EXEG: shift to 2p is to reflect Gk here.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kristus tu, manusia sama ke kotong ju.<bt>Kristus is/was also human like us,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang bunu bekin mati sang Dia,<bt>People killed Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma ais ju Tuhan pung Roh kasi idop kambali sang Dia.<bt>but then God2's Spirit brought Him back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hapaks: once LITERAL: Because Christ also"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">hapaks: once LITERAL: Because Christ also died for sins once, the righteous for the unrighteous, that he might bring you to God, being put to death in the flesh, but made alive in Spirit.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Itu Roh ju ada bawa Dia pi ajar sang roh-roh yang ada takurung dalam satu tampa yang sama ke bui.<bt>That Spirit also took Him to teach the various spirits who are corralled/detained in a place like a prison. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. NIV, HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phulake: place of guarding, prison, underworld,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">phulake: place of guarding, prison, underworld, place of punishment [in Hell] LITERAL: in which he went and preached to the spirits in prison,<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Dong tu, andia orang dolu-dolu yang sonde mau dengar sang Tuhan. Itu waktu ba'i Noh ada bekin kapal bésar. Tuhan ada tunggu-tunggu ko mau lia orang dong bekin iko Dia pung mau, ma dong sonde mau bekin iko. Andia ko cuma dalapan orang sa yang dapa salamat dari itu banjer bésar.<bt>They are the people long ago who didn't want to listen to/obey God2. At that time Gf/Ff Noh was making a/the big ship. God2 kept waiting (expectantly) wanting to see people doing according to His will, but they didn't want to obey. That is why it was only eight people who were *saved from that big flood.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: who formerly did not obey"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: who formerly did not obey when God's patience waited in the days of Noah, during the building of the ark, in which a few, that is, eight souls, were saved through water.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 6:1--7:24</note><v n="21" />Itu banjer jadi satu conto, yang sama ke waktu bosong ada dapa sarani. Itu sarani kasi tunju bilang, Tuhan ada kasi lapás sang bosong dari bosong pung sala, tagal Yesus Kristus su idop kambali. Waktu dong sarani sang bosong, dong sonde kasi mandi sang bosong ko bekin barisi bosong pung badan. Te yang batúl tu, andia bosong ada janji sang Tuhan, ko mau bekin barisi bosong pung hati. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa idop deng bekin yang batúl.<bt>That flood is an example, like when you-pl were *baptised (method neutral). That baptism shows that God2 is releasing/saving you from your wrongs/sin, because Yesus Kristus has come back to life. When they baptised you, they didn't bathe you to clean your body. Cuz (elaboration) in fact/truth, you were promising/pact/pledge to God2 (that you are going) to clean/purify your livers. In that way, you are able to live by doing what is right. [EXEG: “appeal/request to God” OR “pledge/promise to God”? Ex. Summ 1.1; NRSV note: “a pledge to God” LN “a promise made to God from a good conscience.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ EXEG: requesting ?? or testifying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">@@ EXEG: requesting ?? or testifying @@ see if possibilty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eperwtema: request, appeal, make a request"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">eperwtema: request, appeal, make a request for, inquiry, question // pledge, promise, (commitment) LITERAL: Baptism, which corresponds to this, now saves you, not as a removal of dirt from the body, but as an appeal/pledge to God for a clear conscience, through the resurrection of Jesus Christ.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te yang batúl tu, andia, bosong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Te yang batúl tu, andia, bosong ada minta sang Tuhan, ko Dia bekin barisi bosong pung hati.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Sakarang Yesus su nae kambali pi sorga. Di sana Dia ada dudu di tampa yang paling hormat, di Tuhan Allah pung sablá kanan. Ais ana bua di sorga dong, samua kuasa, deng yang pegang kuasa dong, musti dengar-dengar sang Kristus.<bt>Now Yesus has ascended back into heaven. There He is sitting in the most respected place at God's right side. So then the *angels (underling) in heaven, all power/authority, and those who hold power/authority, must keep listening to /obeying Kristus. [NOTE: order changed to avoid relative clause being taken as modifying angels. "Seated" is not in the Gk. text, but is awkward without it. Ruling authorities are usually described as seated in target language.] [NOTE to daughter translations: check how you phrased similar lists in Rom. 8:38-39, 13:1; 1 Cor. 15:24; Eph. 1:21, 3:10, 6:12, Col. 1:11-13, 2:10.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ Recheck Romans and Ephesians. UNS's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">@@ Recheck Romans and Ephesians. UNS's aren't getting /samua kuasa/ can we lexically differentiate? but pegang perenta is restricted to "government" same as in Romans, Eph, Col. and 1 Cor, (also samua ilmu, but not fit here;) Don't want to restrict it to /samua kuasa jahat/</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: who has gone into heaven,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: who has gone into heaven, and is at the right hand of God, with angels, authorities, and power subject to him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus pung orang dong musti idop pantas<bt>Kristus'people must live appropriately</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Kristus tu, manusia sama ke kotong. Tagal Dia su dapa sangsara bam-banya, bosong ju musti siap dapa sangsara, sama ke Dia. Ma inga te orang yang siap dapa susa tagal ta'ika deng Kristus, dia su putus ko sonde mau bekin sala lai.<bt>Kristus is human like we-inc are. Because He has gotten much suffering, you-pl also must be prepared to get suffering, like Him. But remember that a person who is prepared to get trouble/difficulty because being bound/linked with Kristus, he has already decided to not do wrong/sin anymore. [EXEG: NLT] [NOTE to daughter translations: be careful to differentiate /manusia sama ke kotong/ “human like we are ” vs. /manusia yang sama ke kotong/ “human in the way/s that we are”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasxw: suffer sarks: body, flesh, physical|i(1)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">pasxw: suffer sarks: body, flesh, physical<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>ennoia: thought, knowledge, insight, idea, design, resolve, mind, intent, resolution, attitude hoplizw: equip, arm, prepare, protect<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>pauw: stop hamartia: sin<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERAL: Since therefore Christ suffered in the flesh, arm yourselves with the same thinking, for the one who has suffered physically has [ceased from sin/turned away from sinning],</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Biar dia masi idop di ini dunya, ma dia sonde idop bekin sala lai sama ke manusia laen dong. Te dia idop bekin iko Tuhan pung mau.<bt>Even though he still lives in this world, nevertheless he doesn't live doing wrong anymore like other humans. Cuz (elaboration) he lives doing according to/obeying God's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epithumia: desire, longing, passion, lust, bad"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">epithumia: desire, longing, passion, lust, bad desire thelema: will, wish<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>epiloipos: remaining, rest of biow: live, conduct ones life<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>xronos: time, a period of time LITERAL: so as to live the rest of the time in the flesh no longer by human passions, but by the will of God.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dolu dia pung waktu cukup kalo bosong mau bekin jahat apa sa, sama ke orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan. Conto ke: dong ada bekin sambarang. Dong maen serong. Dong iko dong pung kapingin bekin jahat. Dong minum mabo. Dong bapesta liar. Dong bapesta cabul. Dong maen songgo yang bisa bekin kotong pung bulu badan dong badiri.<bt>Previously there was enough/plenty of time if you-pl wanted to do whatever (kind of ) evil, like people who don't know/recognise God2. For example: they do excessively/thoughtlessly (implies evil). They play off-track (sexually). They follow their desires to do evil. They drink drunk. They have wild/untames parties. They have orgies/adultery parties. They play around with traditional worship (in ways that) can make our-inc hair stand on end. [EXEG: I think a number of English translations are missing the clue of the Gk tense-aspect “to have participated in, to have done” in the 1st clause.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="badongko banae = mount (each other)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">badongko banae = mount (each other) ; bapesta cabul = carousing, orgy ; mabuk</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="arketos: sufficient, enough, adequate parerkhomai: go"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">arketos: sufficient, enough, adequate parerkhomai: go by<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>boulema: intention, desire, like ethnos: nation, heathen, pagan, Gentile<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>katergazomai: achieve, do, accomplish poreuw: proceed<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>aselgeia: debauchery, licentiousness, sensuality, shameful excess, indecency epithumia: desire, lust<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>oivophlygia: drunkenness kwmos: carousing, revelry, wild celebration, orgy<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>potos: drinking, drinking party, carousal athemitos: unlawful, lawless, forbidden<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>eidoololatria: idolatry LITERAL: For the time that is past is enough for doing what the heathen like to do, living in debaucheries, evil passions, drunkenness, revels, carousing, and lawless idolatry<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dolu, bosong mau bekin jahat apa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Dolu, bosong mau bekin jahat apa sa, sama ke orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan dong, na, dia pung waktu ada/cukup. Dong bekin sambarang. Dong maen serong. Dong iko kapingin jahat. Dong (minum) mabo barát. Dong pesta-pesta liar. Dong bapaló-ciom sambarang. Dong maen songgo (talebe-lebe yang bekin kotong pung bulu badan badiri).</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Dong omong bekin rusak bosong pung nama bae, tagal dong sonde mangarti akurang ko bosong sonde iko campor deng dong pung jahat yang kalewat batas.<bt>They speak ruining your good name/reputation, because they don't understand why it is that you won't participate mixing/involving (yourselves) in their evil that is beyond the pale/boundary/limits.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ksenizomai: be surprised, amazed, astonished, wonder"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">ksenizomai: be surprised, amazed, astonished, wonder suntrexw: run together, join, plunge into, rushing with, indulge<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>aswtia: debauchery, wastefulness, wild living anaxusis: pouring out, flood<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>blasphemew: slander, blaspheme, verbal abuse, defame LITERAL: In which they are surprised that you do not join them in the same flood of wasteful living, and they slander you.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma inga te nanti dong musti mangada sang Tuhan Allah, yang jadi Tukang Putus Parkara. Dong musti kasi tau sang Dia akurang ko dong idop jahat bagitu. Jang lupa, te samua orang musti mangada sang Dia. Bae orang yang masi idop, bae orang yang su mati dong.<bt>But remember that later they must front up (to authority) to God, who is the Judge. They must tell/explain to Him why they were living evil like that. Don't forget that everyone must front up to Him. Both people who are still living, and people who are already dead.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bae A..., bae B (stok lama)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">bae A..., bae B (stok lama) ; bae A..., deng B... (generasi muda)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apodidwmi: give away, give up, give"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">apodidwmi: give away, give up, give out logos: account, reckoning, reason, word, message<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>hetoimoos: be ready krinoo: judge<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>zaoo: live, physical life nekros: dead person<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERAL: They will give account to him who is ready to judge the living and the dead.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Batúl! Tuhan Allah mau pareksa orang yang su mati dong, sama ke Dia pareksa manusia laen. Te Dia mau lia dong pung jalan idop yang dolu. Andia ko Yesus su pi kasi tau Tuhan pung Kabar Bae kasi sang dong, ko biar dong ju bisa dapa idop yang batúl ko bekin iko Tuhan pung mau.<bt>That's right! God is going to examine the people who are already dead, just like he examines other people. Cuz (elaboration) He's going to look at their way of life previously. That is why Yesus went to tell God2's good News to them, so that they could also get/obtain real life to do according to God2's will. [EXEG: See complexity in Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="euaggelizw: preach the good news, announce"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">euaggelizw: preach the good news, announce pneumati: dey can come alive inside fo real kine<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERAL: For this is why the Good News was preached even to the dead, that though judged in the body like men, they might live in the spirit according to God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong musti jaga deng piara bae-bae samua yang Tuhan su kasi sang kotong<bt>We-inc must take good care of/nurture everything that God2 has given us</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Hari kiamat su deka-deka datang. Andia ko bosong musti pikir panjang deng kalam, ko bosong bisa sambayang deng bae.<bt>The end of the world is coming soon. That is why you must think long (think through implications, be wise), and calm/stable/grounded, so you-pl can pray well/effectively.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="telos: end, termination, cessation, outcome, conclusion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">telos: end, termination, cessation, outcome, conclusion eggizw: approach, be near, be at hand, occur soon<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>swphronew: sound mind, sane, reasonable, sensible, serious, cool head, keep your heads nephw: be self controlled, sober, well-balanced, use self-restraint<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>proseuxe: prayer LITERAL: But the end of all things is near. Therefore, stay sane and sober for your prayers.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Yang pantíng, bosong musti idop basayang tarús satu deng satu. Te biar orang laen bekin sala bam-banya, ma bosong masi bisa bakawan kalo bosong sayang sang dia.<bt>The important thing is, you must live loving each other continually. Cuz (elaboration) even if (the) other person/people do much wrong/sin, nevertheless you can still remain friends if you love him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batamán (older generation) ~ bakawan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">batamán (older generation) ~ bakawan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ektenes: earnest, eager, strong, real, constant,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">ektenes: earnest, eager, strong, real, constant, intense, deep kaluptw: cover, cover up<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>plethos: quantity, multitude, large number LITERAL: And above all, have unfailing love for one another, since love covers a multitude of sins.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 10:12; Yohanis 13:34-35</note><v n="9" />Buka tangan ko tarima orang dari tampa laen manumpang di bosong pung ruma. Ma inga. Jang tarima deng mangomek.<bt>Open your arms to receive people from other places to stay (piggy-back, not permanent) in your houses. But remember. Don't receive them with grumbling.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="philoksenos: hospitable, be kind to strangers,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">philoksenos: hospitable, be kind to strangers, open your home aneu: without<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>goggusmos: grumbling, complaining LITERAL: Practice hospitality ungrudgingly to one another.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Tiap orang yang su tarima karunya dari Tuhan, musti pake itu karunya ko layani dia pung sodara orang parcaya dong. Piara deng pake bae-bae itu karunya, ko dia ada pung guna kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>Each person who has received a *special.gifting from God2, must use that special.gifting to serve/minister to his sibling believers. Take care of/nurture and use well/carefully that special.gifting, so that it is useful for God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hekastos: each xapisma: gift|i(10) (10) |rdiakonew:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">hekastos: each xapisma: gift<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>diakonew: minister, serve, help oikonomos: manager, steward, caretaker, administrator<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>poikilos: diversified, varied xaris: favor, gift<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERAL: As each one has received a gift, serve each other with it as good managers of God's varied gifts.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Conto ke: kalo dapa karunya ajar orang, na, inga te bosong musti kasi tau orang dong pake Tuhan pung Kata-kata sandiri. Kalo dapa karunya layani orang, na, layani pake kuat yang Tuhan kasi. Deng bagitu, samua orang dapa lia, bosong tu, Yesus Kristus pung orang. Tagal itu, dong angka tinggi-tinggi sang Tuhan Allah. Te Dia tu, hebat! Deng Dia pung kuasa ko pegang parenta sonde tau putus-putus! Batúl bagitu!<bt>For example: if (you) get a special.gifting to teach people, na, remember that you must tell/explain to people using God2's own Words/Message. If (you) get a special.gifting to serve people, na, serve using the strength that God2 gives. In that way, everyone can see that you are Yesus Kristus' people. Because of that, they *glorify (elevate way on high) God. Cuz (elaboration) He is great/amazing/awesome! And His power/authority to hold rule/government never ends. That's right/true! [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lalew: speak logia: word, speech, saying|i(11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">lalew: speak logia: word, speech, saying<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>diakonew: serve, minister, help isxus: strength, power, might<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>xoregew: provide, make available kratos: power, rule, sovereignty<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERAL: If anyone speaks, [let him do it] as one who utters the words of God. If anyone serves someone, [let him do it] as one who serves by the strength which God supplies, in order that in everything God may be glorified through Jesus Christ. To him belong glory and ruling power forever and ever. Amen.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong dapa sangsara tagal jadi orang Kristen<bt>We-inc get/experience suffering because (we) are Kristen people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Sodara sayang dong! Jang heran kalo dapa coba'an yang barát. Te itu ada uji bosong pung parcaya. Jang pikir bilang, cuma lu sandiri sa yang dapa coba'an bagitu.<bt>Dear siblings! Don't be surprised if you experience heavy/severe trials/temptations/testing. Cuz (elaboration) that is testing your belief. Don't think that only just you-sg yourself are the only one who experiences trials/temptations like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agapetos: beloved, dear, dear friends ksenizw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">agapetos: beloved, dear, dear friends ksenizw: surprise, astonish, amaze, wonder, think it strange, startled<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>purwsis: burning, fiery, extreme suffering peirasmos: test, trial, temptation, proving, trouble, peril, hardship<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>givomai: be, become ksenos: strange, surprising, unheard of, foreign<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>sumbainw: meet, happen, come about LITERAL: Beloved, do not be surprised at the fiery trial which comes upon you to test you, as though something strange were happening to you.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ma bosong bisa hati babunga, te bosong dapa sangsara sama ke Kristus ju dapa sangsara. Deng bagitu, nanti bosong pung hati babunga batúl waktu samua orang dapa lia Kristus pung hebat.<bt>But you-pl can be glad, cuz (elaboration) you experience suffering like Kristus also experienced suffering. In that way, later your livers will be truly glad when everyone is able to see Kristus' greatness/amazingness. [EXEG: Gk: glory here; CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katho: insofar as, to the extent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">katho: insofar as, to the extent that, to the degree that, as much as koinwnew: share, fellowship, partake of<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>pathema: suffering, misfortune, affliction xairw: rejoice, be glad<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>apokaluptw: revelation, disclosure, uncovering, unveiling dokse: glory<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>xairw: rejoice agalliaw: be glad, exult, overjoyed, outburst of joy, shout for joy<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERAL: But rejoice, insofar as you share Christ's sufferings, that you may also rejoice and be glad when his glory is revealed.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Waktu orang omong bekin hina sang bosong tagal bosong ta'ika deng Kristus, bosong ontong, tagal Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang hebat ada di bosong.<bt>When people speak insulting/slandering/despising you because you are bound/linked with Kristus, you are fortunate, because God's amazing/incredible Spirit is at/upon/among you. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oneidizw: reproach, revile, heap insults upon"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">oneidizw: reproach, revile, heap insults upon makarios: blessed, fortunate<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>doksa: glory, brightness, splendor, radiance anapauw: rest on<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERAL: Since you are insulted for the sake of Christ, you are fortunate, because the spirit of glory and of God rests upon you.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ma kalo bosong musti dapa sangsara, na, jang tagal bosong jadi tukang bunu orang ko, pancuri ko, orang jahat ko, tukang tasosok maso pi orang laen pung urusan.<bt>But if you have to experience suffering, na, don't let it be because you are murderers, or, thieves, or, evil people/criminals, or, busybodies to shove themselves into other people's affairs/business.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasxw: suffer phoneus: murderer|i(15) (15) |rkleptes:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">pasxw: suffer phoneus: murderer<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>kleptes: thief kakopoios: evildoer, wrongdoer, criminal<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>allotriepiskopos: busybody, butting into other people's business, mischief- maker LITERAL: But let none of you suffer as a murderer, or a thief, or a wrongdoer, or a busybody,<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ma kalo orang dapa susa tagal jadi Kristus pung orang, dia sonde usa malu apa-apa. Lebe bae, dong angka puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah, tagal dong jadi orang Kristen.<bt>But if a person experience trouble/difficulty because s/he if Kristus' person, s/he doesn't need to be ashamed/embarrassed about anything. It's better/best if they lift praises to God, because they are Kristen people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Xristianos: Christian, Christ's person aisxunew: be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">Xristianos: Christian, Christ's person aisxunew: be ashamed<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>doksazw: praise, give glory to, glorify, honor, magnify LITERAL: Yet if one suffers as a Christian, let him not be ashamed, but under that name let him praise God,<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Dia pung waktu su datang ko orang mangada sang Tuhan Allah. Dia mulai pareksa dari Dia pung orang sandiri dong pung idop. Jadi pikir sa! Kalo Dia su mulai deng kotong orang Kristen, na, karmana deng orang yang sonde mau tarima Dia pung Kabar Bae? Pasti dong pung hukuman lebe barát, ó!<bt>The time has come for people to front up to God [KM lex: implies face an authority for questioning]. He begins examining from His own people's lives. So (consequence), just think about it! If He has begun with us-inc Kristen people, na, how about the people who don't want to receive/accept His Good News? Surely their judgment/sentence/punishment will be heavier/more severe, ó! [NOTE to daughter translations: lexical choices mangada, pareksa, hukuman and barát all evoke formal examination and resulting judgment.] [EXEG: Grudem points out that the Gk /krima/ focuses on the whole process of judicial evaluation through to condemnation/sentencing. If Peter wanted to focus only on the resulting phase of judgment, another Gk term /katakrima/ is available to highlight that phase. The focus is on accountability and implies purification.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added “dong pung hukuman”"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) added “dong pung hukuman” and note.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaipos: time arxw: begin|i(17) (17) |rkrima:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">kaipos: time arxw: begin<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>krima: judgement telos: end, outcome<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>apeithew: disobey LITERAL: Because the time has come for judgement to begin with the household of God. And if it begins with us, what will be the outcome for those who do not obey the Good News of God?<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te ada tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>Cuz it is written in the Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Kalo orang yang idop lurus sa amper-amper sonde dapa salamat,<bt>“If even a person who lives straight/righteously nearly doesn't get saved/rescued, [EXEG: note this preserves the ambiguity of the Gk. Are we talking about spiritual salvation? Or are we talking about surviving the purification process of judgment? This leaves open both possibilities, flowing from vs.17.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">na, karmana lai deng orang yang sonde toe sang Tuhan?<bt>na, how about a person who doesn't care about God2?</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ais karmana ju deng orang yang idop bekin sala?&gt;&gt;<bt>And, how about a person who lives doing wrong/sin?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="molis: scarcely, with difficulty asebes: ungodly,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">molis: scarcely, with difficulty asebes: ungodly, godless, profane, irreligious, wicked<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERAL: If the righteous man is scarcely saved, where will the ungodly and sinner appear?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te kalo orang yang idop lurus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">Te kalo orang yang idop lurus dong amper-amper sonde dapa salamat, na, karmana lai deng orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan?</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 11:31</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Jadi, kalo Tuhan Allah kasi biar Dia pung orang dong ada dapa susa iko Tuhan pung mau, na, dong bisa parcaya bilang, nanti Dia ju jaga sang dong. Te Dia yang bekin ame sang dong. Dia ju bekin iko apa yang Dia su omong. Tagal Dia jaga sang dong bagitu, andia ko dong masi bisa bekin yang batúl tarús.<bt>So (consequently), if God lets/allows His people to experience trouble/difficulty according to God2's will, na, they can believe/trust that later He will also guard/protect them. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who made them. He also does according to what He has already said/spoken. Because He guards them like that, that is why they can still keep on doing what is right. [EXEG (connector): The Gk is like a participal/gerund-like compound “doing good” in the dative case because it is the object of the preposition “in”. Some English translations interpret the “in” into a “while”, which isn't unreasonable. I can't see grammatically how it could be an imperative. Stripping down the Gk to its bare bones, I see something like: let them commit/entrust themselves/their souls to a faithful/trustworthy creator in doing good. We've explicated the faithful/trustworthy bit from the context as a two-part a) will guard them, and b) will do what He says. And <span class="Italic">because of that</span>, they have opportunity to keep doing the right thing.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agathopoiia: doer of good LITERAL: Therefore,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">agathopoiia: doer of good LITERAL: Therefore, let those who suffer according to God's will do right and entrust their souls to a faithful creator.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nasiat kasi pamimpin jama'at dong<bt>Advice to/for leaders of congregations</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Naa, beta sandiri jadi satu pamimpin. Dolu waktu Kristus pikol Dia pung sangsara, beta lia deng mata kapala sandiri. Nanti ju, kalo samua orang dapa lia Tuhan Allah pung hebat, beta ju mau iko lia itu hal dong deng mata kapala sandiri. Jadi beta mau kasi nasiat sang pamimpin laen dong, bagini:<bt>Naa, [+shift] I myself am a leader. Previously when Kristus carried/bore His suffering, I saw it with my own eyeballs. And later, when everyone is able to see God's greatness/amazingness/awesomeness, I am also going to participate in seeing those things with my own eyeballs. So (consequently), I want to/am going to give advice to other leaders, like this: [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apokaluptw: reveal, uncover doksa: glory, brightness,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">apokaluptw: reveal, uncover doksa: glory, brightness, splendor, radiance<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>koinwnos: companion, partaker, one who shares, partner martus: witness<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>mellw: be about to pathema: suffering, misfortune<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>parakalew: appeal to, urge, exhort, encourage presbuteros: older, elder, a leader among Christians<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>sumpresbuteros: fellow elder LITERAL: So I urge the elders among you, as a fellow elder and witness of Christ's sufferings, and one who shares in the glory that is about to be revealed,<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Bosong sama ke gambala yang piara dong pung domba dong. Jadi bosong musti jaga deng piara bae-bae orang yang Tuhan su kasi sang bosong. Urus sang dong deng bae. Jang urus tagal itu bosong pung tugas, ma tagal bosong suka bekin bagitu. Urus sang dong iko Tuhan pung mau. Jang suka makan ontong lebe-lebe, ma karjá deng samangat ko tolong Tuhan pung orang dong.<bt>You-pl are like shepherd who care for/nurture their sheep. So (consequently), you must care for/nurture well/carefully the people whom God2 has given to you. Manage/deal with/handle them well. Don't manage/handle them because that is your job/responsibility, but because you like to do that. Manage/handle them according to God2's will. Don't like to get undue gain/benefit/profit, but work enthusiastically/with fervor to help/assist God2's people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aisxrokerdws: fond of dishonest profit, desire"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">aisxrokerdws: fond of dishonest profit, desire for dishonest gain anagkastws: by compulsion, necessary<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>hekousiws: willingly, voluntarily episkopew: oversee, supervise, care for<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>poimainw: tend, herd, lead to pasture, protect, lead, guide, rule poimnion: flock<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>prothumws: willingly, eagerly, freely LITERAL: Tend the flock of God that is in your charge, overseeing it, not because you must, but willingly as under God, not for dishonest gain, but eagerly.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="5:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 21:15-17</note><v n="3" />Jang maen parenta sambarang, ko bekin barát orang yang Tuhan su kasi ko bosong urus. Ma bosong musti jadi conto yang bae, yang kasi tunju jalan sang dong.<bt>Don't go bossing people around, to/or burden/oppress people whom God2 has given for you to manage/handle. But you must be a good example, who shows the way for them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katakurieuw: rule, dominate, domineer, be master,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">katakurieuw: rule, dominate, domineer, be master, lord it over kleros: lot, portion, share, those assigned to you, those in your charge<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>tupos: mark, type, example, pattern, model LITERAL: Not as domineering over those in your charge, but being examples to the flock.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Yesus tu, sama ke Kapala Gambala. Nanti kalo Dia su datang kambali, Tuhan Allah mau kasi bosong pung upa, tagal bosong urus bosong pung orang deng bae. Itu upa tu, sonde bisa rusak buang, te dia batahan tarús.<bt>Yesus is like the Head Shepherd. Later when He has come back, God is going to give your reward, because you have managed/handled your people well. that reward cannot spoil/ruin, cuz (elaboration) it endures continually. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="amarantinos: unfading arxipoimen: chief shepherd|i(4) (4)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">amarantinos: unfading arxipoimen: chief shepherd<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>phanerow: show, reveal, appear komizw: bring, carry off, get, receive<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>stephanos: wreath, crown, prize, reward LITERAL: And when the chief Shepherd appears/is revealed, you will obtain the unfading crown/reward of glory<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nasiat kasi orang muda dong<bt>Advice for young people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Orang muda dong! Bosong ju musti dengar-dengar sang jama'at pung pamimpin dong. Bosong samua jang angka-angka diri. Te Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang,<bt>Young people! You-pl must keep listening to/obeying the leaders of the congregation. All of you should not elevate/boast yourselves. Cuz (elaboration) the Scriptures write saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan malawan sang orang yang angka-angka diri dong,<bt>“God2 opposes people who elevate themselves (boast, proud),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Dia suka kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang orang yang randá hati.&gt;&gt;<bt>but He likes to show His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to people who are humble (low liver).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="antitassw: oppose, resist didwmi: give|i(5) (5)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">antitassw: oppose, resist didwmi: give<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>egkomeoomai: put on neos: novice, new, young<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>homoiws: likewise tapeinos: low, lowly, humble, lowly-minded<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>tapeinophrosune: humility, humbleness huperephanos: proud, arrogant, haughty<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>hupotassw: be subject, submit, be subordinated, obey xaris: favor, goodwill, favor<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERAL: Likewise, younger ones, submit to the elders. All of you clothe yourselves with humility, because "God opposes the proud, but gives goodwill/grace to the humble."</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 3:34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Andia ko bosong samua musti inga Tuhan pung kuasa, ko biar bosong jang kapala bésar. Ais lama-lama, pas dia pung waktu, Tuhan mau angka puji sang bosong.<bt>That is why all of you must remember God2's power/authority, so that you shouldn't be arrogant (big headed). Then eventually, just at the right time, God2 is going to lift praises to/for you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kairos: time krataios: powerful, mighty|i(6) (6)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">kairos: time krataios: powerful, mighty<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>hupsow: lift up, raise, raise up, exalt, honor xeir: hand<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERAL: Therefore, humble yourselves under the mighty hand of God that in due time he may exalt you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 23:12, Lukas 14:11, 18:14</note><v n="7" />Angka hati ko biar Tuhan yang urus samua hal yang bekin bosong jadi pikiran. Te Dia ada taro hati sang bosong.<bt>Lift your livers so that God2 is the one who manages/handles everything that makes/causes you to worry. Cuz (elaboration) He is compassionate/attending/caring/placing His liver on you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="angka hati = UNS sarakan, (prayer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">angka hati = UNS sarakan, (prayer is what is intended, but this is OK)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epiriptw: throw, cast melei: it is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">epiriptw: throw, cast melei: it is a care, concern<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>merimna: anxiety, worry, concern LITERAL: Cast all your worries on him, because he cares about you.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sambayang deng angka hati ?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">sambayang deng angka hati ?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ati-ati, ó! Pikir panjang! Jaga bae-bae, te kotong pung musu, andia setan dong pung bos, mau kasi ancor buang sang bosong. Dia mau kodo ame sang bosong, sama ke satu singa yang mara, yang ada cari-cari mangsa.<bt>Be careful, ó! Think long (be wise, think through implications)! Guard carefully, cuz (elaboration) our-inc enemy, that is the boss of the evil spirits, wants to completely destroy/ruin/make everything fall apart you. He wants to swallow you up, like an angry lion who is looking for prey. [NOTE to daughter translation: If mangsa is confusing, ALT: kejar binatang ko makan dia pung daging.] [EXEG: “roaring lion”. In Africa this probably indicates a hungry lion. And the roar instills terror (debilitating fear) in those who hear it. In Kupang/Timor animals that hunt (e.g. dogs) don't bark/roar from hunger, but from anger, when fighting or when cornered (at their most dangerous). So anger is what evokes that this is a dangerous animal out to destroy us. Keep in mind, however, Peter's higher-level message, “the basic command given to us here is (not to cower or to flee but) to stand firm against him. (His bark is worse than his bite, his roar is more than his power to actually hurt us - because we are the Lords'.) We are to stand firm in resisting/opposing him. We are not to weaken in the psychological warfare.” (NS) CHECK what this conveys in your language.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangsa ; *** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">mangsa ; *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="antidikos: opponent, enemy, adversary gregorew: be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">antidikos: opponent, enemy, adversary gregorew: be awake<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>katapinw: swallow, drink down, devour, eat up nephw: be self-controlled, sober, well-balanced [see 1:13, 4:7]<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERAL: Be sober, be watchful. Your enemy the Devil prowls around like a roaring lion, looking for someone to devour.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ma jang taku. Bosong musti malawan sang setan dong pung bos tu. Bosong ju musti batahan ko parcaya sang Tuhan tarús. Te bosong su tau bilang, bosong pung sodara orang parcaya di mana-mana di ini dunya, ju musti dapa susa sama ke bosong.<bt>But don't be afraid. You must oppose that boss of the evil spirits. You must also endure/persevere to keep believing in God2. Cuz (elaboration) you already know that your sibling believers all over the world, also must experience trouble/difficulty like you. [EXEG: “don't be afraid” added at request of consultant to make the higher level picture in 8-9 carry. See note in vs.8.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) “But don't be afraid”"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">*** (2009) “But don't be afraid” added at request of consultant to make the higher level picture in 8-9 carry</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adelphotes: brotherhood anthistemi: set against|i(9) (9)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">adelphotes: brotherhood anthistemi: set against<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>epitelew: lay upon, pay tribute, accomplish, complete, perfect, finish oida: know<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>pathema: suffering pistis: faith<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>stereos: firm LITERAL: Resist him, firm in your faith, knowing that the same experience of suffering is required of your brotherhood throughout the world.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ma inga te Tuhan Allah suka kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong. Dia yang su pange ame sang bosong ko jadi Dia pung orang, tagal bosong su tarima ame sang Kristus. Andia ko Dia mau angka tinggi-tinggi sang bosong, ko bosong bisa idop tarús deng Dia. Ma kalo bosong su dapa susa di ini dunya sabantar sa, na, Tuhan mau bekin bae kambali sang bosong. Dia mau kasi kuat sang bosong, deng bekin bosong batahan. Dia ju kasi bangun sang bosong di fanderen yang kuat.<bt>But remember that God likes to show/demonstrate His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to us-inc. He is the one who has called you-pl to be/become His people, because you have accepted/received Kristus. That is why He wants to *glorify (elevate way on high) you, so you can live continually with Him. But if/when you get/experience trouble/difficulty in this world for a moment/short time, na, God2 is going to fix/heal/restore you again. He is going to strengthen you, and make/cause you to endure/persevere. He is also building you on/onto a strong foundation. [EXEG: Gk: glory here; last sentence explicating Gk ‘establish’ as per NLT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="themeliow: establish, settle you, rest on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">themeliow: establish, settle you, rest on a firm foundation, support katartizw: restore<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>oligos: little (while sthenow: strengthen, make strong<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>sterizw: establish, confirm, prop, make firm xaris: favor<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERAL: The God of all grace, who calls you to his eternal glory in Christ, after you have suffered a little while, restore, establish, strengthen, settle you.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-02-02 04:25:32Z" /></Annotation><v n="11" />Kotong minta ko samua kuasa ada di Tuhan pung tangan sampe salamanya. Batúl!<bt>We request that all power/authority be in God2's hand forever. That's right!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERAL: To him be the power"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">LITERAL: To him be the power forever. Amen.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus konci dia pung surat<bt>Petrus locks/closes his letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Silas<bt>Silas</bt><note reference="5:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Di sini tulisan bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, <span class="Italic">Silvanus</span>. Silvanus tu, Silas pung nama laen. Baca dia pung carita mulai di <span class="Italic">Utusan dong pung Carita</span> 15:22,40.<bt>The Yunani language writings say, <span class="Italic">Silvanus</span> here. Silvanus is Silas' other name. Read his story beginning in <span class="Italic">Story of the Apostles</span> 15:22,40.</bt></note>ada tolong beta ko tulis ini surat pende ni. Dia tu, kotong pung sodara orang parcaya, deng beta pung tangan kanan. Beta ada kasi nasiat sang bosong, ko bosong batahan kuat, te Tuhan suka kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong tarús. Jadi bosong musti tanam kaki ko jang ondor.<bt>is helping me to write this short letter. He is our-inc sibling believer, and my right hand (trusted off-sider). I am advising you, so you stand/endure strong, cuz (elaboration) God2 likes to show His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to us-inc continually. So (consequently) you must plant your feet (be unmoveable) to not retreat/withdraw/pull back. [EXEG: “this IS the true grace of God . Complication by how these lgs express grace as “show good liver/insides”. But OV adjusted to get away from a grey area. /mau kasu tunju/ “likes to show/is going to show” -- /suka kasi tunju/ “likes to show” (avoid /ada kasi tunju/ which could appear to a sufferer to be an untrue statement and is saying something slightly different from the Gk).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tangan kanan = trusted assistant ***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z">tangan kanan = trusted assistant *** (2009) mau kasu tunju --&gt; suka kasi tunju (avoid /ada kasi tunju/ which could appear to be an untrue statement</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="alethes: real epimarturew: bear witness|i(12) (12)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">alethes: real epimarturew: bear witness<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>histemi: stand logizomai: think<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERAL: By Silas/Silvanus, a faithful brother, as I consider him, I have written briefly to you, urging and declaring that this is the true grace of God. Stand fast in it.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Orang parcaya yang bakumpul di kota Babel dong ju ada titip salam kasi sang bosong. Tuhan Allah su pili ame sang dong, sama ke Dia pili ame sang bosong.<bt>The believers who gather in the city of Babel also send greetings to you-pl. God has chosen/selected them, just like He has chosen you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta pung ana Markus ju ada titip salam.<bt>My child Markus also sends greetings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="suneklektos: chosen together LITERAL: She who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">suneklektos: chosen together LITERAL: She who is at Babylon, who is likewise chosen, sends you greetings, and so does my son Mark.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="5:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 12:12, 25, 13:13, 15:37-39, Kolose 4:10, Filemon 24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Kalo bosong bakatumu, na, togor pake ciom manis yang kasi tunju bosong pung sayang.<bt>When you meet each other, na, greet using a sweet/kind kiss/sniff that shows your love.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta mau ko bosong samua yang parcaya sang Kristus bisa idop aman, dame, deng tanáng.<bt>I want for all of you who believe in Kristus to be able to live safe (external peace), at peace (relational), and calm (inner peace).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aspazomai: greet eirene: peace, welfare, health|i(14)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:43Z" status="Information">aspazomai: greet eirene: peace, welfare, health<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERAL: Greet each other with the kiss of love. Peace to all of you that are in Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Saloom,<bt>Saloom,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Petrus<bt>Petrus</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>